animal.description:
If you're reading this, Pearl is still available. Please do not inquire through Petfinder as we can't guarantee a reply. Submit an adoption application here:  www.misunderstoodmutts.org/adopt

Pearl is shy and timid at first, but once she settles in she is a sweet and affectionate lap dog. She loves to snuggle and burrow under blankets, but also likes to explore the backyard and go on walks. 

Pearl has been learning how to be a dog from her foster brother, and would do well with a doggie companion. She’s fine with cats. Since joining her foster home, Pearl has been crate training, potty training, and learning to walk on a leash, and progressing really well. She’s very nervous on car rides and in new places, so she needs a patient human to continue to grow her confidence  exposing her to the world.

Pearl is approximately 1.5 yrs old and weighs 8 pounds.  She is fostered in Bellingham, WA.  Her adoption fee is $425.

We are unable to adopt into Canada unless you have the ability to cross the border.

**Only completed applications will be considered. Please do not inquire through Petfinder as we can't guarantee a reply. Submit an adoption application here:  www.misunderstoodmutts.org/adopt

animal.description:
RED BLUFF CALIFORNIA

KURT IS STILL AT THE SHELTER WITH NO VISITORS!

Kurt is an Anatolian Shepard mix, approx 10 months old and 81 pounds of beautiful dog.  He is current on vaccinations and is heartworm negative.

He is not doing well, he is barking and jumping in his kennel so people cannot see his true self. Please keep sharing Kurt, HE SERIOUSLY NEEDS OUR HELP!

Meet Kurt! His good looks have created interest but he has had no visitors.
You see Kurt is reactive to other dogs in the Shelter and has to be the only dog in the household. Kurt is young and may adjust to other dogs with training. Kurt is very treat and praise motivated!

When you look into Kurt's eyes you see a gentle soul. When you spend time with Kurt you will find he is smart, loyal, loving and can be a playful funny goofball.

On Kurt's outing he walked great on leash, loved the water, likes to both run or walk and is game to just chill on the grass next to you for a couple belly rubs. Kurt knows, sit, shake and wait. Kurt loves car rides and pupichinos! He is mostly quite the polite gentlemen. See video in comments.  

Kurt will on occasion jump for treats or play so will be better suited for older children.  

Hugging Kurt and receiving gentle kisses in return made my heart swell. Kurt is truly a wonderful dog.

animal.description:
Paris was saved from being killed today Monday, January 25th

The shelter believed that she was dumped after her puppies were sold or died. As it was obvious when she arrived that that she recently had a litter and her milk was starting to dry up.

She loves everyone she meets! She's super sweet and very lovey-dovey. She likes to give kisses and enjoys being around people! Happy, playful, tail-wagging sweetheart is who she is. She did well with other dogs on leash. 

Miss Paris is about 5-6 years old. She is a stunning blue brindle girl with the cutest ears! She weighs about 48lbs.

She was far too interested in the chickens at her foster home so we don't think she'll do good with small animals. (However, she hasn't been cat tested)

We would love to see this joyful girl go to a home where she will be spoiled by her forever family. Ideally a family that doesn't mind puppy kisses or a doggy shadow in the home. As we are willing to bet like many pittie/staffe type dogs she will be a velcro doggie and follow you around the house. If you'd like to adopt Miss Paris please apply at our website listed below...


APPLY AT: www.NBArescue.com

animal.description:
Delilah is a 9 month old puppy and you'll know it when you meet her as she has energy to burn. Unfortunately she didn't come from a good home and was left caged for hours on end for months and they gave her up because she was acting like a puppy who didn’t have an outlet for her energy.

She's a very happy girl but definitely a busy girl who is jumpy. She's at that puppy stage where she wants to put her mouth and teeth on everything toys, hands, and sometimes things she's not supposed to. 

She'll need some training with repetitive redirection by placing toys in her mouth to show her what to chew on. She's very playful and love toys so the redirection tactic works well with her. She seems to be teething so with some patience and determination she’ll be the best pup!

Delilah is she already knows sit and listens very well and quickly to that command. She also is crate trained! She knows how to sit and stay and wait for you to put her food bowl down and waits for you to give her the okay. She’s a fast learner and just wants to please you!

 She is mostly potty trained but still has some accidents. Delilah loves people and wants to meet everyone! She just needs a family that can give her and outlet for her energy and work on training with her.

Because she still needs training she isn’t a good fit for a home with small children but older children that can help with training or play fetch with her in the backyard would be great! She loves to play fetch!!!

 Please submit an application via www.NBArescue.com

American Pit Bulls are a misunderstood breed; for this reason, we implore adopters to these beautiful dogs to be very vigilant in training and socialization. This breed is very energetic and will need daily exercise. Because of their strength and energy, apartment living may not be the best fit. This breed can be loving, loyal and very smart. 

The above behaviors and personality traits have been observed while at the Shelter. If this animal was relinquished, information is gathered from the owner regarding behavior. Our wonderful volunteers spend time with these animals and give input on behaviors and traits. However, this description may not be all inclusive to how this animal will act in a loving forever home. Introduction to established family pets should be slow and monitored always. The same goes for children and other family members. Adopting a pet is a big decision and should be thoughtful. We suggest researching different breeds to match traits and personalities to your lifestyle. When adopting a pet, please know that this pet will be with you for their lifetime; patience and consistency will make for a successful adoption.

animal.description:
Maisie is a 2.5 year old mutt! After coming into rescue at a young age, Maisie spent a lot of time in training, working on her confidence and socialization. The world was big and scary but she tackled her fears one step at a time! Now that she has blossomed into a confident girl, she's on the search for her forever home! 

Maisie can be a bit shy when meeting new people however, does great meeting new friends when rewarded with treats! She is very food and toy motivated and works hard to please her people. Maisie does best with boundaries so she can know what to expect from her foster family and avoid any sort of guessing games. She is working on her obedience training and her future family should be committed to expanding her list of known tricks! She loves to learn and gains more confidence with every new command. She does fantastic in her crate and is potty trained. She enjoys going for walks and playing in the backyard. Maisie LOVES toys and will pull every toy out of the toy bin before selecting the perfect toy to play with. She likes lounging on the couch with her foster family and playing fetch with her toys, although she's still working on bringing them back! Maisie prefers to eat in her crate, but comes right back out after she's finished to continue playing. While Maisie is a bit nervous in the car, she's getting more and more comfortable with each ride. Small children's loud noises and quick movements can be quite intimidating, so Maisie is looking for a home with older children who can be respectful of her space during her acclimation period. She would love a home where she can be your one and only pet.

Maisie is a happy and playful pup who can't wait to find her forever home. If you want to make her a part of your family, apply online today! Her adoption fee is $250.

animal.description:
Darling Beth is available for adoption again! <3

"Beth seems to match the energy of the room. In my house she is very active and tries to play with my cat all the time. But when the cats are out of reach, she seems to be calmer. She is a big hugger, loves belly rubs and snuggles. She also will follow her person everywhere and loves to go places with them."

Beth originally came to us when she had her babies in the shelter. Sadly, the shelter is no place for newborns, and she lost all but two by the time they came into rescue with us. Thankfully her pups Rip and Chief Rainwater have been adopted and are doing great in their new homes. Beth ended up being heart-worm positive so she stayed with us a few more months before eventually being adopted. Here, she became a Colorado girl and has a best friend in the form of a cat. Beth is really missing another doggie playmate which is why she is coming back into rescue. She can be pretty energetic, and her owner doesn't feel she can give her the exercise she needs. It was decided that she would come back with us, so we could find her a more active family with another playful dog. 

Beth is a 2 year old female Labrador Retriever mix. We are not sure what else she is mixed with. She currently weighs around 70lbs and won't be getting much bigger. Beth is a people lover. Actually she loves everyone, people and animals alike. She is friendly when meeting new people. She is a social butterfly and does great in public settings. Beth's playful is on the more active and playful side. For the most part, she matches the energy of the household, though. Beth has excellent house manners and can be trusted with free-roam of the house. She has not chewed up anything in her fosters home. 

Beth isn't a fetch player, but she does like chasing the dogs as the go fetch the ball. We are unsure if Beth is a water dog or not. Beth isn't a big fan of toys, but does like to chew on bones. Beth has not shown to have any signs of food aggression in her foster home. She also does not resource guard things. Beth will give you hugs when she gets excited. Beth rides well in the car, and does good on road trips. Beth does well on walks, but could use some more working with. She gets easily distracted by squirrels and tries to take you with her to go meet them ;) Beth can be vocal at times. When her fosters or away or at night, Beth has free-roam of the house and does great. Beth is potty trained, but does not have any experience with being kenneled. 

Beth is a really amazing girl, and anyone who adopts her is going to be so in love with this girl. Before you apply to adopt her, here are some things to note

-Beth does great with other dogs. She loves to play with them. It would be best if her new family had another playful dog in her new home. However, if her family were on the more active side and home most of the day she would be fine as an only dog. 

-Beth does good with cats. She does try to play with them, especially if there are no doggie friends present. 

-Beth does great around kids of all ages. With that said, they need to be respectful of her space. She would not appreciate being lied on, her ears/tail being pulled, etc. 

-Beth really needs a home with good sized yard, and/or active people. She likes to watch what's going on outside and will bark if anyone or anything is on the other side of the fence (good guardian). She loves to chase bikes at the dog park. If a bike rides by on the opposite side of the fence, she will race it (and she always wins). 

-Beth is being fostered in Englewood, CO. Adopters are responsible for picking up their new dog, even if they are out of state. 

Hopefully at this point you have decided that Beth is the girl for you! If that is the case, you can apply to adopt her at https://www.pyrpawsandfluffytailsrescue.com/adoption-app

Her adoption fee is $225 and that will include her vaccinations, spay, and microchip. It will also include her heart-worm treatment. She will also be current on heart-worm and flea/tick prevention.

animal.description:
"Hiya! My name is Jellyfish, but you can call me Jelly or Fish. To be honest, I'm not picky as long as I'm getting attention. I am an 11-12 month old Pittie that came to SVASC as a stray and was never reclaimed, so now I'm hoping to start over fresh with you. What do ya say? 

When I first arrived at SVASC, I was terrified of everyone and everything. It's hard coming to a new place with all sorts of scary noises and smells. Thankfully, shelter staff are willing to take things slow and let dogs blossom at their own pace... and that's really what I did! After about 2 weeks here, I am a totally different dog and am full of spunk. I am still pretty nervous around new people, but I do warm up and am worth getting to know. Please just give me some time when you meet me and don't get too scared away by my bark. I promise that I'm a big love!

I do get on pretty well with other dogs and may even be more confident if there was another confident, well-socialized, and established dog in the home for me to learn from. I would love to meet any future pals before going home please. I would do best in a home without any small kiddos or kids younger than teenagers. Once I warm up, I have all the energy of a young Pittie and turn into an adorable wrecking ball, so I would likely not be suited for a home with small kids. 

My adoption fee is $125 to an approved adopter. If you would like more information on me, please give SVASC a call at (540) 943-5142 or stop by the shelter during open hours. SVASC is located at 1001 Mt. Torrey Rd. Lyndhurst, VA."

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Name: Topaz

DOB: 1/21/2015

Weight: 25

Adoption Fee: 375

Hey everyone! My name is Topaz. I am heartworm positive, but don't let that deter you! I will be completely healthy again very soon. Since I have heartworm right now, I'm available through the foster to adopt program.

Since Topaz is heartworm positive. He/She will need to be treated in at our clinic in Princeton.

Heartworm treatment consists of 3 injections. The first injection will be in roughly 30 days after coming into rescue. The the 2nd and 3rd injections happen 30 days after that. When a dog is going through heartworm treatment, they should be on "restrictions", meaning a lot of lap time, crate time and always on a leash. Heartworm disease is NOT contagious, it is transported via mosquitos.

Here is a great article explaining what heartworm is and how it's treated: https://www.heartwormsociety.org/pet-owner-resources/heartworm-basics

An adoption application is the best way to show your interest in an animal.

All Ruff Start dogs and cats are spayed/neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccines, microchipped, dewormed, and on monthly flea/tick and heartworm prevention (dogs) as well as heartworm tested (dogs).

Ruff Start Rescue is a foster based rescue. Animals are located in homes throughout Minnesota. We do not have a facility where animals are kept.

Ruff Start Rescue Adoption Policies: http://www.ruffstartrescue.org/info/display?PageID=11744

animal.description:
Pops is a 6-year-old mixed breed rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed/neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. animal.description:
Melvin is a 2-year-old English Bulldog rescued from a high-kill shelter. This dog is current on vaccinations, microchipped, 4dx/heartworm tested, and spayed/neutered. This dog is also tested with other dogs, kennel-trained, and housebroken. Melvin would do best in a home without young children and medium to large-sized male dogs. We would love for you to meet this dog and see if it might be a good fit for your home. 

The first step to adoption is completing an adoption application on our website at www.bounceanimalrescue.org. Pending approval, your application is valid for 1 year, and you will be eligible to request a hold on an individual animal. The hold does not require that you adopt the animal, but ensures you get to meet and make an adoption decision prior to other applicants. Hold times cannot exceed 5 days. Also pending approval, you will be able to acquire foster home contact information, so you inquire on personalities of specific animals.

***COVID-19 Update: While we typically host weekly Saturday adoption events, in order to follow the CDC's recommendation for COVID-19 protocols, we will be suspending our weekly Saturday adoption events until given the clear. Adoptions for individual animals will occur by private adoption appointment and/or adoption handoff. Appointments and handoffs are scheduled pending staff, foster home, and vetting schedules. Because we are 100% foster-based, adoption appointments and handoffs are only offered for individual animals. When adopting at an appointment, please be aware that you will be taking the animal home that day. We can not hold animals to be picked up at a later date.

Due to CDC's recommended COVID-19 protocols, we are highly encouraging foster homes and adopters to speak with one another via phone or video chat to ensure compatible matches and limit in-person contact. If meeting in person, our foster homes are encouraged to wear masks, socially distance, and choose an outdoor meeting spot. Should you want to proceed forward with the adoption, all adoption paperwork, medical records, and adoption fees are to be completed electronically. Quick and low-contact animal handoff is also being encouraged amongst foster homes and adopters. As always, we include a one-week trial period with all our adoptions. ***

Please note, we do not have the ability to process adoption applications at our adoption events, so please plan accordingly. If an application is submitted past 5pm on Monday-Thursday, it will begin review the following day. If submitted on Friday-Sunday, it will begin review on Monday. It takes approximately 48-72 hours for an application to be processed.

For additional questions regarding meeting this dog please contact us via text/email at 970.699.6772, or contact@bounceanimalrescue.org. We apologize for any inconvenience, but due to a high volume of inquiries, calls and voicemails regarding adoption will not be returned.

animal.description:
Jig is an 80 lb. shepherd mix who made the trip to Michigan from Humane Society of the Delta in Arkansas. He is a majestic boy, a gentle giant and great with humans of all shapes and sizes. He is a bit of an introvert and likes lots of alone time throughout the day. That all changes when it's time to go for a walk -- he gets SO excited and will jump up as soon as you make a move for your coat. And jump is not an exaggeration, he really gets some air! 

Jig loves all the interesting sights and sounds outside and sprints to find the source when he smells something interesting. Although he enjoys being introduced to new people, he is not a fan of most dogs he meets while out and about, and shows his fearfulness by barking at them.

Jig can't get enough of digging treats out of his snuffle mat. It's one of his favorite things to do. Every now and then he gets in the mood to play and when he does, he's all in! Some of his favorite things to do are playing tug of war, chasing balls, and trying to catch treats in the air.

Jig is heartworm positive and will have his first treatment at the end of January, and will need a family who will support him through his second treatment at the end of February. Costs for the treatments are paid for by Hearts of Hope.

Jig is a super sweet boy who you can't help but love! He is neutered, chipped and up to date on vaccines. His adoption fee is $250.

I like other doggos and those kitties, too, and wouldn't mind having a furry playmate--as long as they're low-energy, like me. My foster's teaching me all about this crate-training thing. animal.description:
Meet Jan (short hair) and Marcia (long hair)!  These two bonded sisters came to us as strays in rough shape.  Luckily, a good Samaritan brought them to the emergency clinic then they were transferred to us for continued care. 

Jan and Marcia are the perfect pair.  They love each other fiercely and will cuddle, play, and groom each other.  They also love people and adore being pet and picked up.  Their sweet and gentle nature make them so easy to love!

Unfortunately, Jan was found with extensive burns across the right side of her face.  We do not know what happened to her.  Luckily, her skin is healing well, but her damaged eye had to be removed surgically.  She is much more comfortable now!  She also had several mammary tumors removed surgically.  She has heart disease and her remaining eye also needs medicated drops to treat dry eye. We require her adopter to have a close relationship with their vet to monitor her health closely. Despite all of her medical conditions, she is still full of life and deserves to find a home that will spoil her and her sister!

Are you looking to add these sisters to your life?  Call the Saratoga County Animal Shelter at (518) 885-4113 ext 0 to make an appointment.

animal.description: It’s time to introduce you, formally, to the Mega E Three! Trigger, Jordan, and Sherman are 10 week old, male, pure bred German Shepherd pups. These boys are extra special and are looking for extra special homes. Trigger, Jordan, and Sherman are the 3 surviving puppies of 5 born to the litter with Mega Esophagus. Once the breeder and his vet discovered what was going on, it was too late for 2 of the pups. But he was able to sustain these three boys until he could find a rescue to accept them. Once with MHCR, the boys took a trip to CSU in hopes their Mega E was the operable kind. It was not. ?. The good news is, when properly managed, puppies and dogs with Mega E live long and wonderful lives. Their forever families will need to understand Mega E and embrace the routine of upright feeding. Luckily, we’ve been fortunate enough to secure Bailey chairs for the pups that will accompany them to their forever homes. Please, do your research. Make sure you have the time and commitment to care for these pups! We know their cuteness may cause uncontrollable urges to apply - trust us - we get it! They’re irresistible! https://vcahospitals.com/know-your-pet/megaesophagus.  You can apply for Sherman at https://milehighcanine.org/forms-and-applications/mhcr-adoption-application/.

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE: WE ARE REQUIRING SNOWY'S FOREVER HOME HAS PRIOR BREED EXPERIENCE & A FENCED YARD*

Snowy is a 2 year old neutered male Great Pyrenees who weighs 80 lbs. Snowy was rescued from death row after being dumped at a high kill shelter by his former person. This beautiful boy is so sweet despite everything he's been through. He loves when you pet his fluffy coat and scratch behind his ears. Snowy has been doing very well in his foster home and is slowly gaining some much needed weight. His forever family will need to be patient with him and provide him with a schedule so he can get the hang of home life, but he really is learning things quickly. He has been good with other dogs and didn't seem to mind cats. He has strong breed tendencies and will be an amazing guardian for his family. Snowy will need a forever family that is familiar with guardian breeds and a large fenced yard for him to stretch his legs and patrol. His ideal home will be on the quieter side without a lot of traffic in and out. We adore this fluffy marshmallow and have promised him the loving forever family he deserves... could it be yours??

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
**Adoption Pending**

Meet Boone!  Boone is an 8 month old male mixed breed puppy who was pulled from a hoarding case with 20+ other dogs, and is now looking for the perfect forever home! 

Boone and his litter mates are all very sweet dogs who simply need an owner who can help them learn "how to be a dog". By that, we mean some of the skills and experiences that most dogs learn throughout their lives are often lost on dogs who were living in situations like this. They were likely not exposed to the majority of the outside world, and all they knew was how to survive alongside their pack mates. Because of this, Boone will require a patient, loving and understanding family who will devote lots of time and attention to his needs. While we realize it's sad to think about the life they lived before, it's important not to dwell on that, and to simply give him the best chance at becoming a happy, healthy adult dog by simply focusing on the future! 

Boone will require training as he does not yet know how to walk on a leash, or any commands quite yet. He is also not potty trained yet, but we recommend utilizing a crate to help him with this transition. With plenty of consistency and reward, we know he'll catch on! Basic obedience classes in a setting with an instructor who is skilled at working with shy dogs is also recommended. 

Boone will likely do best in a home with another dog. He is used to living in a pack, and will probably follow the lead of the dog that he lives with. We also think he'll do fine around children and kitties as long as he's properly introduced.

If you have the time, patience and love for a dog who needs a little extra TLC, Boone would be happy to join your family! Boone is neutered and fully vaccinated. His adoption fee is $150.00

animal.description:
Nubby- Male/Neutered Lab/Rottie Mix  Color: Black & Tan 10 months old 58 lbs.
ID# D-40054

Nubby is a 3-legged dog who was found as a stray at about a month old, with only a nub for his right front leg, (most likely born that way). He has a very sweet demeanor, loves people and gets along with other well mannered dogs. He is hesitant and timid, he needs confidence building, especially since he's trying to adjust to living in the shelter. He and his sister, Niecee were given up by their owner after 9 months because they were more active than the senior dogs in the home, which was causing the senior dogs stress. Nubby loves kids but needs a family with lots of patience and understanding to give this guy time to fit in and adjust. He needs a secured , fenced yard for some supervised exercise and play time, and the rest of his time, needs to be indoors. He appears to be housebroken. We have listed the best age of kids for him to be about 10 years old. 

Nubby is current on basic vaccinations including Bordetella, been dewormed and is microchipped. He has tested Negative for Heartworms. 

Nubby is already neutered and his Rabies vaccination is current until May 2021..

For more information, please contact the City of Corsicana Animal Shelter at (903) 654-4928. The shelter is open Mon, Tues, Thurs and Fri from 12:00pm - 6:00pm and on Sat from 12:00pm - 4:00pm.

She is also playful and outgoing. We are thinking this beautiful girl is a Labrador Retriever mix around 1 year old.

Misa is friendly with all of us humans but may act a little shy at first, but give her just a little time and she will best your new best friend! She is also shy around children and thus don't recommend her for a family with young active kids but an older child (teenager) in the home might be fine if patient, relatively quiet, and not overbearing. She is friendly with other dogs and would make a great addition to a household as the only dog or as a buddy to existing family dogs. Misa is only mildly interested in cats and for the most part tends to ignore them.

We don't know much about her upbringing and a potential adopter will need to go slow with Misa, work on socialization, give her plenty of exercise, and provide training and structure as she transitions to life in a forever home. She would do best in a low-key household without much foot traffic.

Misa needs an adopter who is committed to keeping her world small until she starts to settle in. The adopter should plan to limit visitors to the home, leave the dog at home (crated - not loose!) rather than taking her to parties, soccer games, dog parks, etc, and focus on building a bond through structure and moderate obedience training.

She doesn't appear to have much training and is just getting started on house training, crate training, and leash training and so far, so good! A fenced yard would be ideal so Misa could run and play safely, but if that's not available she'll need lots of leash walks and opportunities for off-leash play in a fenced area.

Misa is a happy girl who just wants a loving forever home. Can you make her dream come true? Fill out an application today and let her know that you'd love to have her join your family!

Misa's story: She was found as a stray with two littermates.

Adoption Fee: $585

To apply for this dog, fill out an adoption application on our website: www.sosarl.org/aa/

**Additional info you should know - For most of our dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each of our dogs as an individual and do our best to describe and place them based on personality not breed label. Some dogs may not yet be in New England, nor ready for immediate adoption. There may be additional vetting, quarantine, waiting periods and/or fees depending upon your state of residence. If you have questions or concerns on any of this, you can discuss this with your Adoption Counselor.

animal.description:
**Adoption Pending**

Meet Bubba! Bubba is an 8 month old male mixed breed puppy who was pulled from a hoarding case with 20+ other dogs, and is now looking for the perfect forever home!

Bubba and his litter mates are all very sweet dogs who simply need an owner who can help them learn "how to be a dog". By that, we mean some of the skills and experiences that most dogs learn throughout their lives are often lost on dogs who were living in situations like this. They were likely not exposed to the majority of the outside world, and all they knew was how to survive alongside their pack mates. Because of this, Bubba will require a patient, loving and understanding family who will devote lots of time and attention to his needs. While we realize it's sad to think about the life they lived before, it's important not to dwell on that, and to simply give him the best chance at becoming a happy, healthy adult dog by simply focusing on the future!

Bubba will require training as he does not yet know how to walk on a leash, or any commands quite yet. He is also not potty trained yet, but we recommend utilizing a crate to help him with this transition. With plenty of consistency and reward, we know he'll catch on! Basic obedience classes in a setting with an instructor who is skilled at working with shy dogs is also recommended.

Bubba will likely do best in a home with another dog. He is used to living in a pack, and will probably follow the lead of the dog that he lives with. We also think he'll do fine around children and kitties as long as he's properly introduced.

If you have the time, patience and love for a dog who needs a little extra TLC, Bubba would be happy to join your family! Boone is neutered and fully vaccinated. His adoption fee is $150.00

You must leave a message so that we can return your call to schedule an appointment. Listings are updated on a weekly basis.

Don't be fooled by his serious expression, Dutch is a sweet and social dog around 10 years of age. He was surrendered to the Franklin Township Animal Shelter due to his old age --but he is a healthy, active dog who enjoys playing fetch and tug of war! Dutch knows basic commands and walks relatively well on a leash, but can be stubborn when he sets his scents on something. He would benefit from additional training in this area. Dutch can go to a home with older children, and cats if he is introduced to them properly. He can go to a home with other dogs, but would have to meet them first.

Our adoption fee for dogs, cats, kittens, and rabbits is $60 per pet with a discount available for adopting two animals together. Cats, dogs, rabbits and kittens from the Franklin Township Animal Shelter are spayed/neutered. Cats, dogs, and kittens are microchipped, and up-to-date on all age-appropriate shots prior to adoption. Cats have also been tested for feline leukemia and FIV and dogs have been tested for heartworm.

animal.description:
MEET FABIO!!

THIS DOG IS SLATED FOR EUTHANASIA by the County Shelter-- NEEDS IMMEDIATE FOSTER/ADOPTER.

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. He is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4499290.

Doesn't Fabio have the most soulful eyes? When Fabio first came to the shelter, he came in with some wounds and they were not sure if he was hit by a car. He has recovered perfectly from his wounds and now he's ready to go home. He used to be shy when staff or volunteers took him out of his kennel to go for a walk but now he knows when someone comes, he gets to get out and sniff and explore his surroundings. He walks easily on a leash. He can be coaxed with treats, he loves them, and then he continues on. He knows how to "sit". He didn't like it when another dog did a face-to-face introduction and the shelter recommends that he be the only dog in the home. Fabio should go to a home with older children that understands he's been through a lot in his young life and needs to decompress and get used to a new home and new family. If you would like to meet Fabio, please bring the family and come and see him soon. Fabio has been at the shelter for over 60 days now and he is showing signs of stress by jumping up and down in his kennel. He cannot take being in the shelter much longer and would love to go home!!

If you are interested in saving this pet, please reach out via this link: https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/foster/BPAZ/Dog

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG.

animal.description:
Parker is a 5 yr old male shepherd/golden retriever mix that weighs 78# (vet says he needs to drop 5#).  He is a very handsome dog, and also very nice. Parker is friendly with the people and dogs he has met.  He gets along with the cat – although the cat thinks that his bushy tail is a toy for him to play with.  The cat will sit on a chair waiting for Parker to walk by so he can bat at Parker’s tail – Parker ignores this attention.

He really enjoys his frequent trips to the dog park. At the park, he is very independent and will join up with a group chasing a tennis ball – often carrying it back to the person throwing it.  He will wander with a group of dogs, but usually not rough house or run with them. Although he does not come when called at the dog park, he will come when called at home. He gets along well with the resident dog - rough housing sometimes, play boxing, running, parallel sniffing.

Parker likes his food.  The two dogs are fed in separate rooms to allow the other dog enough time to eat.  The cat’s food in on the mantel where Parker can’t get at it.  He takes treats very roughly, so just to be safe he probably should go with older kids.  However, he does “sit” when asked and easily catches a treat thrown to him. During the summer he would take tomatoes off the vine – green and red tomatoes.  Smartly, he left the hot peppers and herbs alone.

At night or nap-time Parker sleeps on the carpeted floor at the foot of the bed - sometimes he moves to the bare floor probably because he was hot.  He can get up on the bed, but doesn't sleep on the bed or even nap on the bed - perhaps because the resident dog has taken the spot.  He is usually somewhere in the same room with his foster during the day – laying by the desk or the couch. Thus far, he has only been left for 4 hrs, and is so well behaved that he doesn't need to be crated. Foster thinks he would be OK for up to 6 hrs, but not longer. 

Doesn't bark a lot - but will join in with the resident dog at barking at a noise outside the house.  Parker’s bark is more of a talking noise. People walking by the house frequently comment on how good looking he is.  He usually greets people, often putting his feet on the top rail of the fence (a 4-foot fence). Parker likes to ride in the car, usually sitting in the front seat.  After a good run at the dog park he usually curls up in the back seat.  Opening the garage and the back door is all the invitation he needs to jump into the car. Walks nicely on leash. Does some shedding - not bad - might need some brushing.  Laid back, friendly to all, he is easy to have around. 
 It appears that in the past he somehow injured his head because of the small scar on his lower eye lid, a kink in the left ear and an unusual look to one eye.  His left eye looks like it has a cataract - something the vet calls a partial incipient cataract ( covers less than 15% of the lens and doesn’t affect vision)-  he has good eyesight and can chase balls and catch a tossed treat.
Parker came from Texas, and had a cough that was initially treated as kennel cough. The cough persisted, and with more testing he was ultimately diagnosed with lung worms (not common in MN).  The worms are gone (a  Baermann fecal test for Lungworm done on 11/12/20 was negative) , but there has been some scarring and inflammation to his lungs.  He is treated with a daily dosage of Prednisone, probably for his lifetime, which means he drinks a fair amount of water. This medication requires a prescription, but is relatively inexpensive.  The dose of prednisone is 20 mg/day, and with a script is very reasonable at CostCo - with membership, 30 tabs (a 1 month supply) is $8; without membership is $14 (you can use the CosCo pharmacy without a membership).  He should also be on a heartworm preventative year round. 
Parker is neutered, and current on distemper and rabies vaccinations. He tested negative for heartworm disease. His microchip is registered to Second Chance. The adoption fee for this sweet, mellow, easy going dog is $295. Call 651-771-5662 if you have questions or would like to meet Parker. A vet reference is required.

All of our rescue are in foster homes and family pets.Thank you for choosing to adopt not buy. 
Koda is a two-year-old purebred Rottweiler. He is neutered, up-to-date on vaccines, microchip and house trained.  He needs an experienced Rottweiler home only. He needs a fenced in yard only no exceptions. He needs a large young playmate, he cannot be an only dog. And we prefer a home with no cats because while he is good with 1 of my cats he chases the others a d he does have a prey drive.  He is extremely protective of his people so he needs socialization to be continued after adoption. We do not know his exact past but he does suffer from some anxiety and is currently on anxiety meds which helped him a lot. He is fostered with four other dogs, three cats and three children ages 14, 11 and 6.  We do not want to place him in a home with children under the age of 5. He is a super cuddle bug at night time and must sleep in bed with you. He is almost perfect with his crate training. Before putting in an application you must speak with his foster. If The adoption proceeds you will put in an application and set up multiple meetings once your application is approved. 

His adoption fee is $400.00

animal.description:
Looking for that special friend that will always make you smile? I just may be him! My name is Biggie and I am 11 years young. I’m a handsome fawn Pug with an amazing personality that you just can’t help but love!

My foster family describes me as an “outgoing gentlemen” and that is the truth! I am a well-mannered happy guy that loves making friends, human and doggy. Obviously, I am amazing and you will love me so fill out an application ASAP to meet me: Biggie, the gentlemen Pug!

Roxi is pretty pittie mix approx 1 yr 45lbs. 
Very sweet and friendly, loves to give kisses and play fetch too. She's a smart girl and knows sit, but will need someone to be a strong leader for her. She would do best in a home with older children (12 yrs +)
Roxi seems ok with cats although slow intros with cats in a home are always required, and if there are other dogs in the home a meet and greet will need to be arranged. 

If you are interested in adopting please email dogadoptions@thesanctuarypa.org to fill out an application and questionnaire.
Please be aware that we are all volunteers and we do not pre-approve applications nor do we hold onto applications, so please make copies of our application and questionnaire in case another application is chosen and you want to submit an application again in the future for another available dog.
We are open every Saturday to the public  from 10-2 to meet our dogs. Dog adoptions will not take place during that 10-2 timeframe and applications will only be taken on our available dogs that day. 
Also please do not bring your own dogs during our Saturday open hours.

PLEASE NOTE: At this time we are following CDC guidelines and practicing social distancing and wearing masks in our buildings 

Hope to see you soon!!

animal.description:
Presley is gaga gorgeous but will need a experienced understanding home.  Presley is a kind hearted boy, who takes "velcro dog" very seriously. This is probably because this is where he feels safest, you see Presley has a fear of well EVERYTHING. We aren't sure why Presley jumps at his own shadow but needs a family that will boost his confidence, and run his anxious energy out. Long fast paced walks or runs will be best for his mental health. He is FULL of energy and will act ten feet tall barking at neighbors and other animals defending his perimeter.  He is potty trained but needs you to remind him to go and stand with him until he does. Otherwise his buzzing energy gets the best of him and he forgets. He will most likely always be a very skittish boy who loves people and hates loud sudden noises. He doesn't have much interest in toys or fetch but will settle down for a good chew showing he's still a young pup. Presley will not thrive in a home with shared walls as he howls and cries for some time after you've gone. Presley is 3 1/2 years old. 

Interested in adoption? You can find our application on our website at www.austincockerrescue.org  We are not currently accepting out of state applications.

animal.description:
An adoption application must be completed in order to adopt one of our available pets. To access our application please click on either of the following links:
For PDF Format:
http://www.oxleypc.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/fhas-adoption-application-pdf.pdfFor Word Document Format:
http://www.oxleypc.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/fhas-adoption-application-word.docx
Upon completion of the application please email the completed application to fhasadoptions@gmail.com. You can type your name on the signature line, save the application and then attach the application to an email to us. Please make sure the application is completed in its entirety. If you have any questions please do not hesitate to ask. A volunteer with Faithful Hearts will contact you within 1-3 days once application is submitted and our adoption committee has an opportunity to review your application. If you have further questions please contact (478) 231-6942. Thank you for inquiring. Black Jack is a black lab/golden retriever mix. He is eight years old but is still a very playful and energetic fellow. He is current on his vaccines, been neutered and started on his monthly heartworm prevention. He was given up by his owner because he wanted a smaller dog. You couldn't find a sweeter dog! If interested in giving this handsome fellow a home and need more information call 478 231 6942.Faithful Hearts Animal Shelter, Inc.
P.O. Box 5014
Eastman, GA 31023478-231-6942
https://www.faithfulheartsrescue.org/

Our mission is to provide safe and humane shelter and to relieve pain and suffering for unwanted, stray and abused animals. Further, to facilitate the placement of these animals in desirable homes and promote responsible pet ownership.Faithful Hearts Animal Shelter is a 501(c)(3) public charity. Our organization was incorporated for the prevention of cruelty to animals and to eliminate the causes of animal suffering. Adoption Process & Fees: We generally require a $150-$200 adoption fee for adopting dogs and we have an application that must be completed and approved prior to adoption. Adoption fees may vary. Contact us for more information on why we charge a fee at all and how our application process works.If you would like to make a tax deductible donation to Faithful Hearts you can do so through Paypal at the button below, or by check or money order at our mailing address listed above. We thank you very much for your support!

animal.description:
Jax, 1 yr neutered male husky mix. Extremely loving, loyal, playful, gentle. Jax had a family in a very small NE Oklahoma rural community who did not have time for him. Jax loves people and loves attention. His foster home includes an aussie female and beagle male mix. They both love him and love their playtimes. There are also 2 cats - Jax would love to chase and play with them, but they are very dog savvy and don't really give him a chance. He is learning to give them their space. There are also 2 horses and he gets along with them as well. Jax stays in the house when his foster mom is home as well as overnight. He stays outside in a pen when no one is home. Jax is good on a leash - jumps in and out of the pickup on command. -He knows sit and is learning stay. He is very gentle for his size. He does love to run outside but always comes when called.Fostering and transporting to places where there is a need for adoptable animals, saves lives, its that simple. 

IMiami Animal Alliance's goal is to be the premium go to place to find your new family member! We work carefully with our Veterinarians and foster families to prepare our pets to be a healthy and happy new family member! 

Our adoption donations cover our medical cost, food and all transport costs. 

All pets are up to date on vaccines, Spayed or neutered and micro-chipped. 

Local Oklahoma adoptions donation fee is $175 for dogs 

Dogs transported fee is $325 

Cats and kittens are $85.00 local, $100 if transported 

at times the fee may be adjusted for a special dog.

animal.description:
Let's meet Magic...he is about 12 weeks old and about 18 pounds and just a fun chunky boy. We estimate he will be a medium size dog maybe 40-50 pounds. He was rescued after being abandoned in the country and brought into the rescue to get medical attention and learn how wonderful it is to be an inside dog and to be loved the way he should. He loves playing with all and any toys he can. He has been working on his puppy manners and does sit and down with some encouragement and takes the treats very well. He currently plays with his sister, Dream and two other dogs. He has no problem keeping up with them. He lives with two human foster siblings as well and they love on him lots. So he is used to action in a busy household. Magic has learned stairs and with little help can get on the couch for cuddles. He is being crate trained for sleep, naps and potty time.
We will continue to work on potty training in the coming weeks. 

Magic has had his 2nd round of shots and will be ready to meet you by the end of January. 

Magic's 3rd round of shots and neuter are included in his adoption fee. Lets get Magic his furever home! 

Applications are at https://bit.ly/codys_adoption_application.

 Cody's does not adopt puppies under the age of six months into apartment homes.

Let's meet Dream...she is about 12 weeks old and just a little sassy girl. She was rescued after being abandoned in the country with her 3 brothers and brought into the rescue to get medical attention and learn how wonderful it is to be an inside dog and to be loved the way they should be. We are thinking she will be a medium size dog, estimating around 40 pounds. She loves playing with all and any toys she can. She has been working on her puppy manners and does sit and down with some encouragement and takes the treats very nicely. She currently plays with her brother, Magic and two other dogs. She has no problem keeping up with them. She lives with two human foster siblings as well and they love on her lots. So she is used to action in a busy household. She has learned stairs and with some help can get on the couch for cuddles. She is being crate trained for sleep, naps and potty time. We will continue to work on potty training in the coming weeks. 

For a meet and greet with Dream please fill out an application and our team will be in touch. 

Her 3rd round of shots and spay is included in the adoption fee. She will be ready to meet you by the end of January. Let's find her the best furever home.

Applications are at https://bit.ly/codys_adoption_application.

Cody's does not adopt puppies under the age of six months into apartment homes.

animal.description:
Newton is a sweet 3 month old puppy, very smart and curious with a soft plush smooth coat. --and thos green eyes ! He is growing fast and learning new things every day. He loves to be with his foster Mom and play play play with his foster brother. He is an active puppy and will need an environment with a large yard and plenty of mental and physical stimulation. He likes his people to be home, and would like a big brother or sister that will help show him how to dog.

Newton knows sit and down and is working on no and leave it. He has started introductions to the leash and enjoys exploring in the back yard. He is improving on his house training and sleeps all night in his crate. He also has morning and afternoon naps in the crate, as well as an hour or 2 "office" time with his foster Mom. He is all puppy and will help with the laundry, sleal your slippers and your heart.

Newton needed to get caught up on his shots and get rid of some unwelcome hitchhikers picked up when his litter was dumped in the county. He is doing great now and ready to find his furever home.

Applications are at https://bit.ly/codys_adoption_application.

Cody's does not adopt puppies under the age of six months into apartment homes.

animal.description:
Diego and Dora were found as strays together and we don't know if they were raised together (they aren't very old) or just become extremely bonded. But they do seem to need each other!

Beautiful Dora is approx a year old. Even being out on her own with her friend Diego, she has such a sweet, happy and easy going manner. That's not to say she doesn't like to play because she does and still shows that puppyness! Diego has such a loving spirit and really loves being around people. He is a pretty chill guy mot of the time but only being about 9 months old (he's a big guy), he still gets pretty excited about everything. Both of them do well with other dogs, always waggin their tails in welcome and they seldom bark. They both know to wait to go potty outside and are very gentle taking treats and food.

This is from their trainer/foster: "DIEGO needs DORA more then she needs him. She will at least go potty without him, but then she wants right back in with him, and the reunion is as if they spent days apart. DIEGO, however, cannot function without his sister. They are so dependent upon each other, its sad to see them always looking for the other when I pull them one at a time to work with them. Their lives have not been very consistent, so the bond between them is even stronger. Having each other is something they could always count on. I cannot separate them, I feel like that would be detrimental to their psyche and would forever change who they are. There has to be someone out there, with 3 or 4 kids, that needs a couple of playful pups...."

We do offer a foster to adopt program and working with our trainers if you feel you have a home that would benefit from having a great "two for one" new family members! Please visit our website at www.carerescueok.org for our adoption application.

animal.description:
This sweet girl is Cheers, she is a Beagle mix we believe around 2 yrs old. She was in dire need of rescue along with her puppies sadly, and our foster went in to help her. She is actually the mom to the NY Countdown litter, yes the ones that look like labby pups, lol. She did a great job with her babies and now she is ready to come to WI and find her very own family to love her. She is doing fairly well with her house and leash manners and may need just a little tweaking with this is all. She is a love of people she is a girl who loves to be coddled and loved on. She does fine with other dogs and loves to play around some or find a nice cozy spot to relax and take a snooze, she is a pretty lowkey girl. She is now ready to come to WI and find the good life here, if interested in this little girl an online application can be found at SandiPaws.org
Thank you for your interest in a Sandi Paws Rescue, Inc. Please visit our site at sandipaws.org for more information on our organization or to fill out an application to adopt one of our pets. You can find information for volunteering o. our site as well.

animal.description:
Welcome, welcome, hello, please come closer - I'm Milo and I really like having people near me. I also like toys and playing. I know basic commands like sit, stay and down. I am hoping my new family will teach me more commands. I like to learn and I am a smart boy. My foster family says I am a loveable boy and I sure do enjoy attention. I'm happiest when I can account for my people and they are with me. I can get nervous when I don't know where my people are and hope my furever family will work with me so that I can learn to be more confident if my humans aren't with me. 

Did I mention that I'm a good kisser? Do you have room in your home for a friendly, smart boy who wants to make his humans happy? Please click on my link for more info and let my friends at Demi's know that we should have a playdate.

If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website - https://demisanimalrescue.com/demis-adoption-application/ 

All dogs are spayed/neutered, mircochipped, heartworm tested (if over 6 months old) and up to date on vaccinations (combo shot, bordetella, rabies(if age appropriate) )

animal.description:
Laker, who knows the name Gracie, was adopted and lived in the home for two years before being returned for her bad behaviors. We highly recommend setting up obedience training as soon as she goes home so there can be a smooth transition into your home. While she has lived with other dogs, they did not get along well. She was around one child on occasion and did okay with that child. She likes to guard her food, toys, treats, and is a grouch when she is woken from her sleep. Once past those quirks, she is a loving dog, who wanted her owners attention and time. We are guessing her loyalties to her owner are what made her act like she was the boss of the family/pack, which is a positive if properly trained! DOB 12/30/17 weighs 93 pounds...All pets have lifetime sanctuary at Haven of the Ozarks. If they cannot remain with their adopter, they must be returned to the Haven.

Puppies under the age of 6 months - $125

Rivet
Male
DOB: 4/11/2020
Weight: 60lbs
Breed: Lab/Mastiff mix

Hi! My name is Rivet and I am the sweetest most loyal pup searching for my forever home! I love all things in life including long walks with my human followed by a relaxing nap! I am a very well behaved fella who enjoys all the fun toys like bones, Kongs and stuffed everything; but be warned, I love to tear out all the stuffing to find that squeaker! I love humans; older ones in particular and get along well with other dogs! I relish in a good playmate from time to time! I also get along with cats!
I consider myself quite the smart pup who knows a few commands such as sit, shake, lay down and currently working on mastering stay. I am also house trained and crate trained. I walk really well on a leash and barely pull on the leash while we enjoy a stroll around the neighborhood!

I am excited to find my very own forever family who shares the same things I do in life!

If you are interested in meeting the handsome, Rivet, apply to adopt at www.causeforcanines.org Adoption fee is $300
Children must be 8 years old or older
Must be an Ohio resident 25 years old or older

animal.description:
Hi friends! Lets get to the meet-n-greet, shall we? My name is Toby and I hail all the way from Tennessee. I came to Nebraska on a plane! Im an easy going guy that loves people and to tap dance. Yes, I have moves! The smart people guess that I am around 4-5 years old and weigh about 30 lbs. I currently am undergoing treatment for heartworm, but will get through it soon. 

You could say that Im a special guy! You see, in my life prior to rescue, I was a stray for awhile and people say I was probably hit by a big metal thing on wheels. I have some nerve damage and hip dysphasia that causes my back end to not quite do what I want it to. It doesnt stop me though! I run around the yard, go on walks, go up and down stairs, and even climb up on a stool to get on my chair. My foster mom has been taking to a nice vet that does chiropractic adjustments. They are helping me not hurt so much so I can work on getting strong. I probably will always have some issues, but regular adjustments and exercise will help me be the best I can be! 

I get along with kids and other dogs, but they will have to understand I have some limitations. I love to be lifted into your bed at night so I can cuddle up, but will sleep on the floor if you have a comfy bed there. I have moved around lately, so I do have a little separation anxiety when you leave. I do whine and bark while you are out, so an apartment probably wouldnt be the best house for me. Kennels are ok, but Ive been good when foster mom leaves me out and seem to do better while you are gone. I am potty trained, but sometimes I have a hard time holding it for a long time. I feel bad when I have an accident, but with my nerve issue when I have to go, I have to go.

From his fosters: Tobys zest for life is contagious! He loves baths and being pampered. A good blanket for him to snuggle into is a necessity. Toby is probably the sweetest Beagle you could ever hope to meet. There is something really special about this little boy. Please consider him for your forever dog! 

Toby is neutered, current on shots, microchipped, and currently undergoing heartworm treatment. If interested in adopting Tennessee Toby, please fill out the application at www.bassetandbeagle.org. His adoption fee is $350

animal.description:
My name is Cooper and I am searching for my forever family! My ideal family would be loving and let me snuggle on the couch and possibly in bed with them. A family that will play ball and take me on walks and help me lose some weight. You see, in my short 2 years I have been allowed to gain too much weight, like a LOT of weight. I should be around 45 pounds and instead I am a whopping 80 pounds! 

I love all people, especially if they pet me but I would prefer kids that won't tease me or hang all over me. I will paw at you to let you know I need love! I love to run around with toys and play fetch. I'm good with all dogs. I'm living with a pack of foster fur siblings that range in age from puppy to senior but I can occasionally get a little growly if food is involved. My foster mom feeds us in our own kennels so that no one has any problems; however, I am good when we all sit for treats. 

My foster mom was told that I can play a little rough with cats and I like to sit on them but I haven't done that with her cat. I am house trained and recently I have been using a doggy door to go outside to potty. I have figured out how to slide the sliding glass door open if I need to go in or out and the doggy door is locked but my foster dad gets upset because I don't close it behind me! I am ok in a kennel, right now I sleep there at night, but it is not my favorite place to be. I will only go in if a treat or food is involved and I will give a couple of barks to let you know that I am not happy about being in there before I settle down. 

Since my foster mom has put me on a diet, i have started to counter surf. I try to do this when she's not looking because I really don't like to upset her, I am a pleaser at heart. I am up to date on my vaccinations, neutered, microchipped and ready to go to my forever home. If you think that could be you, please apply at www.bassetandbeagle.org. My adoption fee is $350.

animal.description:
Blackdog Club is a facility-based rescue. We are open to the public Wednesday-Sunday between 10-6. An appointment is not required. 

If an adopter wishes to bring a current pet for a meet/greet, please send vet records showing the pet is UTD on all vaccines prior to your visit to blackdogclub@outlook.com

The adoption fee includes spay or neuter, microchip, age-appropriate vaccines, rabies vaccine, fecal test, deworming, and heartworm test. Dogs are treated if heartworm positive. All dogs are UTD on heartworm/flea/tick prevention. All dogs are health screened and vaccinated by our vet, Family Pet Animal Hospital or Quality Care Animal Hospital.

We do not know if our dogs are house trained. They are crated overnight. 

Shorty 2 is a recent addition to the BDC family. His pictures are deceiving.... he's a dwarf. This dude is so stinking cute. He looks just like a yellow lab on a Basset Hound body. Shorty is a very loving boy that craves attention. He tested well with small children. He walks good on a leash and enjoys playing with toys. We do feel he would do best as the only pet. Estimated DOB: 01/20/2019. Current weight: 48 lbs. 

This pup tested heartworm positive at the shelter. Blackdog Club's protocol for treatment is 30 days of Doxycycline and heartworm prevention, then 2 injections 24 hours apart. This cost is covered by our organization.

animal.description:
KIRA wiggles over to greet you :-) She loves to play and is very affectionate.  She's beautiful and smart. Gorgeous blue eyes.

Her adoption fee includes her spaying, vaccine series, rabies, deworming, microchip. She was born Sept 26, 2020.

** Do you live in our adopting area? ** Do you have another young playful friendly male dog of similar adult size? ** If yes to both questions, then please proceed with the application process below! :-)

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please. Puppies MUST adopt to families that have another young friendly playful dog of similar breed size when grown. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

KIWI AND LIBBY are BONDED sisters who are Terrier mixes and are approximately 2-3 yrs old! Kiwi is the smaller sister and she was born with a cleft lip which impacts her appearance only. Because it’s only cosmetic and Kiwi is such a loving and happy little girl, we chose to not pursue surgery for her…we  actually think it makes her even more precious! Her sister, Libby is a bit bigger but is just as sweet as she can be. I can’t emphasize enough just how special these two girls are. They love each other and everybody else! They walk well on a leash, they are dog friendly, cat friendly, people friendly, and children friendly! They are high energy and always in motion and they love to play! Very dog park friendly pups. 

Kiwi – 2/3 yrs old and weighs 9.8 lbs – Terrier mixes
Libby – 2/3 yrs old and weighs 13.5 lbs – Terrier mixes 

Sister facts:
• House trained using a doggie door 
• Leash trained and loves to walk
• Small dog and cat friendly – both submissive with other dogs
• Both are high energy
• Kiwi and Libby are both microchipped, current on vaccines and spayed 
• Must be kept together and not split up. They are completely bonded. 

Characteristics
Loving, Playful, sweet, adorable, Cute, shy!

Bacon's adoption fee is $200; he is microchipped, up to date on vaccines, and will be neutered prior to finalizing his adoption. Some of our pets are in foster care and not located at the shelter. If you are interested in a specific pet, contact the shelter at (618) 939-7389 to arrange a meeting.

If you would like to provide a foster home, or foster-to-adopt home, during Bacon's heartworm treatment, Helping Strays will provide everything you need; the medical care, crate, food, etc. Foster-to-adopt would be a great way to get to know him. animal.description:
Manthanne is an approximately 5 month old female Catahoula Cur mix who weighs approximately 35 pounds.  Manthanne and her Mom came into Cafa after being found wandering near the plant nurseries on Forrest Hill Louisiana.   Manthanne plays well with all dogs she meets.   She is a beautiful pup with crystal blue eyes and red and black leopard pattern fur which are both common of the Catahoula Cur breed.  

The Catahoula Leopard Dog is a medium-large, short-coated dog, known for its many varied coat and eye colors and patterns. The word catahoula is of Choctaw origin and is translated to mean “sacred lake.” Catahoulas are the only breed of dog to have historically originated in the state of Louisiana. The breed requires firm guidance and early socialization, as they can be independent, territorial, and protective. For the same reasons, they do not allow mistreatment and will assert themselves in self-defense. Once they know their place in the family unit, they are affectionate, loyal, and gentle. Also called the Catahoula Hog Dog, they are used as stock dogs, bay dogs, tree dogs, watchdogs, guard dogs, and of course as loyal companions.  

She is learning to figure out how to walk on a leash.   She will require basic obedience, crate, leash and house training.  She is a super smart and friendly pup who will make a great pup for a loving home. 

Adoption fees details: 
Puppies - Adults $ 550, Seniors $375. These adoption rates include transport from Alexandria, Louisiana to designated New England adopter pick up locations and NE foster homes using either Rescue Road Trips, Pets LLC or CAFA Transport. If you do a search you will see that this is a very reasonable adoption fee and comparable to other rescues. Adoption fee breakdown:Adoption Fee:   $  365.00Transportation Fee:  $ 185.00MA and NH only--Quarantine fee if applicable:  $125.00

Medical details:
All our dogs are altered (spayed or neutered), DHLPP, rabies, Bordetella, Heartworm tested with negative test results, microchipped, treated for parasites and on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention. A health certificate is issued by a licensed Louisiana veterinarian.

Adoption details:  
In some instances, a meet and greet is not possible before adoption unless we have a foster home in New England available. Available for a Meeting confirms the dog is in a NE Foster home and available for a meeting in the city state provided.  Most times our dogs get adopted before a foster home becomes available - and if so, they go straight to adopters home. Foster parents talk to adopters and feel confident that this will be a match before our dogs are transported up. Also if by some chance it is not a match we have a safety net in place as we ask that adopters to let us know that it is not a match and we direct you to take the dog to a foster home or boarding kennel once that is arranged. If necessary, we will ask you to foster the dog until a foster home can be arranged. 
Transport details:Rescue Road Trips (rescueroadtrips.com), Pets LLC (petsllc.net) or CAFA Transport will deliver our precious pups on commercial rescue animal transport to designated locations.  The fee is 185.00 which IS INCLUDED in your adoption fee already.**Rescue Road Trips, was featured on The Today Show - view it at http://www.today.com/video/today/55034556#55034556

MA and NH RESIDENTS:
If you are a Massachusetts or New Hampshire residence, an additional fee of $125.00 will apply due to State quarantine fee requirements. If the dog is in a foster home in MA or NH, this fee will be added in the adoption fee regardless of where the adopters home is located making the total adoption fee $675.00 for puppies and adults $500.00 for Seniors, otherwise the full adoption fee for all other states is $550.00 for puppies and adults and $375.00 for seniors. This includes a 48 quarantine, recheck by a MA licensed veterinarian, and issued a MA health certificate.

Visit all our available dogs at www.cenlaallianceforanimals.comWe update and add dogs frequently.

We hope to help make a difference in a rescue dogs life into loving responsible homes.

Hi, my name is Charlie. I was formerly known by my friends as Brownie. I just turned 5! I'm super smart, and I know "sit", "paw", and "stay" -  they trained me well! My favorite pastimes are playing tug of war with my people or a good game of fetch. I'm very good at it, and I love it when there is more than one toy so I can drop one at your feet and chase the other. I usually bring it back too! 

I am a little shy around new people. I take a bit to warm up but once I'm comfortable I am the most affectionate and loving girl you will ever meet. I would do best in a home with an experienced dog owner who has no other pets but me and no kids. I also would like a house where I have lots of rubber toys and a big comfy dog bed to sleep in! 

If you would like to meet me, please fill out an online application at sarlnh.org.

animal.description:
All of our foster dogs are kept in individual homes. Go to our website Bayareasiberian.org to get the foster home contact if you do not see it in the bio.Hi everyone! Meet Roma

Roma is a very shy but sweet 6mo old puppy. She spent the first few months of her life in less than ideal circumstances causing her to be fearful of most things. She is now with a foster family and has been doing her best to overcome her fears of being outside.
Roma needs a family with a lot of patience that can help show her how to be confident.
She would not do well in a home with young children since she is easily startled. She's met various dogs with no issues. She does well ignoring the pet rabbits at her foster family, and has seen cats but is not interested in them.

Roma currently knows the commands; sit, kennel, go potty, and touch.
She does take a while to warm up to a new family and still isn't 100% comfortable with her foster family but is doing her best. Roma LOVES other dogs and is most confident with the security of an older dog to teach her how to behave. We cannot rehome Roma to a home with another dog under a year old to avoid over attachment to another puppy.Go to BAYAREASIBERIAN.org for contact information on the foster dog.
