Scroll down to learn more about this pet:

***
Bichon and Little Buddies is open only

by appointment with a completed application.
Dogs in foster homes require an appointment and approved application to meet. The application is online at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog If a dog is listed as available, then we are still taking applications - no need to email or call to ask about the status. Note: The forms that Petfinder or Adopt-a-pet has to inquire about the dog is not our application application. Our form must be filled out to be approved to adopt a pet.***

Covid-19 Precautions:

Until further notice, Bichon & Little Buddies will be doing all meets and adoptions by appointment only. To be able to control the number of people at the shelter at one time, we will be suspending our open hours on Thursdays. If interested in adopting, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come meet the dogs you are interested in.

About this Dog:

Name: Sammy

Breed: Shih Tzu-Poodle type mix

Approximate Age: 7 yr

Gender: Male

Weight: around 20 lb

Adoption Fee: $400

Why in Rescue: Owner Surrender

General Profile: Please fill out the adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog if you are interested in meeting one of our dogs.

Sammy sadly lost his home when his owner wasn't able to care for him any longer. He has been with us for awhile since he wasn't adjusting well and didn't want to bond with the caregivers at the shelter. But he has made huge strides recently, and now happily goes for walks with volunteers. He is very food motivated, so treats help! He is a timid dog, so will need a patient adopter who will help build trust and a loving bond with Sammy. He will need work on housetraining, especially after being in the shelter, but he is worth the effort. He was very loved by his previous owner and we know she misses him and would love for him to be with a loving family. He is going to need a home with no young children. He did live with another dog, so may do well with another small dog. If interested in meeting Sammy and learning more about him, please fill out the pre-adoption application so we can see if you might be a good fit for him.

We do our best to evaluate the dogs while they are with us, but they sometimes act different in the shelter environment than they do in a home. If you are interested in any of our dogs, please fill out the pre-adoption application and we will set up a time for you to come and meet them.

If considering adopting a former breeding dog, the following article is good to read to help you understand the special needs these dogs may have. http://www.nowisconsinpuppymills.com/mill-survivors.html

Adoption Procedures:

1. Completely fill out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog. We will be checking with your vet if you have had pets, calling your landlord (if any) and checking a personal reference, before we contact you about visiting the adoptables. Any missing information may have us moving onto another application.

2. If you application is approved, we will contact you to come meet the adoptables that you are interested in.

3. If it is a match, you will complete the adoption contract and pay the adoption fee. Please be prepared to take your adopted pet home when you come meet him/her. In most cases, you will be able to take the pet home the same day. If all the vetting hasn't been done yet, we will hold the pet for you until the vet work is completed.

4. If you have filled out an application and we haven't contacted you within a week, we may have missed your application, the pet may have been adopted by another applicant, or you may have been missing information on your application. You may contact us to find out the status of your application at this time. Please give us a week to process your application before contacting us!

The adoption fee through Bichon and Little Buddies Rescue is $200 - $475 depending on the age of the dog, which includes Wi State Sales Tax. Included in this fee is your new companion who will be spayed/neutered, have a current Certificate of Veterinary Inspection (as required by state law), current on age appropriate vaccinations, heartworm tested and started on preventative, microchipped, and dewormed. Other medical needs will also have been taken care of, such as dentals and treating ear infections.

To assist you and your new pet in adjusting to life together, you will also receive an 8 week age appropriate obedience training course at For Pet's Sake Dog Training for $50 (up to $200 value). You may opt to take Puppy Kindergarten, Adult Beginners, Small Dogs Big Hearts, or Shy & Reactive Dog Class. You must start the class within 90 days of adoption for the reduced fee. For more information on the classes visit www.forpetssake.cc

All dogs are seen BY APPOINTMENT ONLY. Many are in various foster homes getting extra one on one attention getting them ready for their new homes. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application. Bichon and Little Buddies is run by volunteers who have full time jobs in addition to the hours they spend with the rescue dogs. Having an application on file assures us that the potential adopter is really interested in adopting a dog. It also assists us in placing dogs in homes where both the dog and new owners are happy. The application puts you under no obligation to adopt a dog from Bichon and Little Buddies.

The Dog Pre-Adoption Application can be found at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog

Thanks for thinking about adopting your new pet!More important information:

***We are a Wisconsin based rescue and do not ship our pets. If you are considering adoption you must be willing to drive to meet and adopt the pet, as well as bring the pet back to us if the adoption doesn't work. We adopt primarily in WI and IL, but will consider applicants in MN, IA, and MI.***

***Please do not set up an appointment to meet the animals until you are ready to take your pet home. If the meeting results in a match, you can often take the dog/cat home the same day or within a couple days if the medical care hasn't been completed. We are not able to hold pets for adopters beyond this time. Thanks for understanding.***

***While we hope all of our adoptions lead to permanent homes for the animals we place, sometimes things just don't work out. We do have a 30 day trial period. For the first 30 days, if you or Bichon and Little Buddies decide that the adoption isn't a good match for either the humans or the pet, the adoption fee will be refunded minus $50 within 30 days of the return of the dog. Bichon and Little Buddies also requires adopters to return the pet to us at any time that they are unable or unwilling to care for the animal anymore.***

***We do not show dogs/cats without an appointment. The first step in adoption is filling out the pre-adoption application at http://www.bichonrescues.com/pre-adoption-form-dog Please do not call/email until AFTER you have filled out an application.***

animal.description:
Bubu: silver/blue male, neutered, natural tail and ears. 17", 25 lbs. Fully vetted. Rescued from shelter.

My name is Bubu but I have been called many things including Bubba and old guy. I answer to most things and just love to come to you for attention. When my foster picked me up they weren't really sure of my age. Well, I'm definitely an older gentleman, probably about 10 years old, but I don't like to admit it or act like it. 

I really don't know who my parents are or my breed, but my foster Mom calls me a Heinz 57, whatever that means. She thinks there is min pin, French bulldog, and lab, but I can tell you I’m 100% cute!  I am a healthy dog and I have the vet records to prove it. I have many more years to enjoy. I don't take medication and I am a real gentleman.  

My favorite thing I love to do is get petted, go for walks and eat soft morsels of food. My foster Mom thinks I am just the sweetest old man ever and I like to reward her compliments with filling my bed with all her lose clothes and toys she leaves for me. Don't worry, I don't do anything with them. I just love to hold them close. 

She also has two other dogs that I think are okay. The small one I don't care about, she leaves me alone, but the larger one can make me nervous so I will give her a little growl sometimes to get her to go away. My foster Mom doesn't like that though and tells me to stop. I will listen because if I don't, she won't pet me, or let me sit with her, so I chose to listen.

I am looking for someone to give me the best years of my life where I get as much attention as I please.  I would love to go on daily strolls and possibly car trips to check things out with you. I don't mind other dogs as long as they respect my space but would be fine being the only one for you. 

If you can make sure that I have my regular dog food mixed with wet food and get some dog jerky for treats, we may be a match made in heaven. I just love that and even though my teeth look great, I would prefer to eat my food that way.  I am ready to be spoiled and comfortable for many years to come and make you the happiest human ever.  Please won’t you fill out the application now and ask for BuBu?  You won’t regret it – I promise, Love, BuBu

Note: Bubu is located in Nevada County, CA and we will not fly this boy.

If you wish to adopt, please fill out our IMPS Min Pin Adoption Application
If you have previously submitted an Application form, there is no need to re-apply.
For more details, contact Rebecca: minpinlove_imps@yahoo.com  

IMPS is a non-profit rescue organization that does not have a viewing facility to which you can come and meet the dogs available for adoption. All of our dogs are in loving homes in foster care. Arrangements can be made with the foster parent; however, it is a requirement that the Adoption Application be completed and approved first.

If you wish to adopt, please fill out the IMPS MinPin Adoption Application go to:  http://www.minpinrescue.org/home.html 

Please visit our website by going to: http://www.minpinrescue.org

animal.description:
Rugar is about 3  yrs old, but acts younger.  A chocolate lab mix. He came from the rodeo as a working dog. We think he spent a lot of time in a kennel because he HATES to be in one now. We  try to walk him at least 2 miles a day. He pulls on a leash and could benefit from a no pull harness. Off leash, he will wander and needs a fenced yard. Rugar is afraid of the dark,  probably from being at the rodeo, and has some separation anxiety.  He needs a home where someone is home most of the time.  He will scratch doors and get out of crates when left alone.  
Rugar is being fostered with 5 other dogs  from a pug to a 70 lb hound. He does fine with males and females. Rugar will guard toys and bones from our dog that steals from others. He only reacts when she actually tries to take it from him, and is easily redirected. We also have  several cats.  He will chase a cat if it runs. If it doesn’t run, he will slobber all over it till it wishes it had.  He likes toys that squeak, He is very food motivated which helps with training.  He knows “sit”.  
We don’t have kids in the house but I would recommend a home with children over the age of ten. He’s not aggressive, but he will jump when excited. He sleeps on the couch next to the wood burning stove. He’d try to counter surf and get into the trash, but he hasn’t in two weeks. He improves daily and is a very quick learner. He would do best in a home with dogs, cats and older children. He would also be fine as an only dog.

Please use
To adopt - https://form.jotform.com/92314840069154

animal.description:
We literally JUST took into rescue two awesome Beagles, found as strays, running together, in Lauderdale County, TN. Both Tipper and Piper are listed here on Petfinder. TIPPER is such a looker! He is not a large Beagle but a solidly built Beagle, all 40 pounds of him. He is estimated to be about 2 to 3 years old and is just so handsome. He has clean teeth and GREAT bloodwork! He has an ear infection that we have already started treating. Unfortunately, he is heartworm positive, but he will be fully treated. He has been given medicated baths. Since everything looks so good on Tipper, we have just neutered him and all went well.  He has been dewormed, given doses of Heartguard Plus and Nexgard. 

Because he is heartworm positive, we are NOT offering him for regular adoption till he completes heartworm treatment  in May. What we WILL do is approve a foster-to-adopt home for him where the family fosters him through heartworm treatment and is given priority to adopt him, once he completes heartworm treatment. Our fosters must complete the same adoption application we require of regular adopters and be approved. 

If you are interested in fostering-to-adopt Tipper, offering him a forever home, foster-to-adopt is the only way to have him in your home before he completes heartworm treatment in May. We have 3 of our dogs in foster-to-adopt homes right now. Please email Diana at dmoore2003@bellsouth.net and request our adoption application. We can arrange a greet and meet after your application is completed, returned to us, and approved. 

We must tell you that our Beagles are very popular and are adopted or fostered-to-adopt very quickly. So, if you are interested in Tipper or any one of our Beagles, you should apply now.

animal.description:
This dog is being fostered in Dallas TX and must be adopted within the Dallas, North Central Texas or the southern Oklahoma area.

NAME:              Rio
GENDER:         Male (Neutered)
AGE:                  About 3-6 years
WEIGHT:         4.5 pounds
DOGS/CATS:   Gets along with other small dogs, Unknown with cats
CHILDREN:     Should be fine with older, mature children (13 and older)

Say hello to Rio, a handsome, 4.5 pound boy with the softest reddish-tan coat.  He is between 3-6 years old and so sweet and loving!

In late October, we received a call asking if we would be willing to help with a hoarding situation where there were over 30 Chihuahuas.  We drove 1-1/2 hours south of Dallas and took several of those dogs into our program.  Rio was one of those dogs.

Rio fit right in with the other dogs in his foster home and gets along well with all of them.  He loves to snuggle and nap with them while his foster mom is working.  He has discovered some of his foster siblings’ small, plush toys that fit in his mouth, and he loves to carry them around and play fetch with them.

Rio adores his foster mom and loves to give her kisses!  He loves snuggling in her lap or getting up on the back of the sofa and resting his head on her shoulder while she watches TV.  He also likes to sleep in the bed with her at night under the covers.  He is a good bed buddy!

Rio is potty trained and will do his business outside (if it’s not really cold or raining) or use a pee pad.  He has had a few accidents in the house, but this has gotten better as time has gone by.  He is a well-behaved boy and listens to verbal corrections.  If he is unsure of a situation, he can become a little anxious but is easily reassured.  Because he has the potential to be a “door darter,” Rio is crated when his foster mom leaves the house.  And while he is fine being crated if his foster mom is at home, he will howl for quite a while when his mom leaves.  For this reason he is not apartment appropriate.  As he has become accustomed to being crated when his foster mom leaves, the howling has lessened some.  He will climb out of an expen.

Rio is between 3-6 years old. He is generally a calm, quiet and well-behaved boy.  Because of his small size, he must never be left unattended in the backyard and the yard must have a secure, wooden fence.  His ideal home would be calm and moderately active, with a family who spends a lot of time at home.  A work at home family would be perfect!  Rio does not bark a lot, but will if he hears a noise or the other dogs bark.  We believe he would do best in a home where there is another small dog.

Rio is being fostered in the Dallas/Ft. Worth, Texas area. Our CRT adoption form can be found at: http://www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application/

Rio is spayed, micro chipped, up-to-date on shots, HW negative, on heartworm prevention and recently had a dental.  He is ready to join a loving family – could that family be yours?

This dog is a CRT rescue. Reference checks, adoption contract and $270.63 adoption donation required ($250 adoption donation and $20.63 Texas Sales Tax). Note: as of 1-1-20, the Texas State Comptroller office is requiring all rescue groups to collect sales tax on adoptions, even though we are all 501c3. We are all fighting this, but for now, have been told it is non-negotiable.

As part of our mission to reduce the number of unwanted and sick dogs, we require that all current pets are spayed or neutered, current on vaccinations and taking heart worm prevention. Applications will not be considered if one or more of these requirements are not met.

After filling out an adoption application (found at http://www.chihuahua-rescue.com/adoption-application/), please email DFWCoordinator@chihuahua-rescue.com if you are interested in this dog. Please be sure to read about our adoption process and then fill out an adoption application before emailing the contact person.

animal.description:
Hi! I'm Alfie! Have you ever heard the saying, "great things come in small packages? Well that's me! I'm a tiny little guy but I have the sweetest heart. I might be very shy at first, but once I come to trust you, you'll be my person! My foster mom calls me her shadow! Wherever she goes, I go! 

I'm great on the leash and I love to play with toys! My FAVORITE activities are napping and snuggling. I LOVE when my humans work from home. That means I get to snuggle on their laps all day! Oh and I love car rides and going places with my humans. You need to go on a coffee date? I'm your man. My dream would be to travel the world in one of those doggy carrier backpacks.

I'm looking for my furever home and I hope that's you!

Alfie is a Male Chihuahua / Terrier Mix that we estimate to be around 1.5 years old and weighs 11 lbs.

He seems like he might like to 'play' with cats but that might too much for any kitty! He's pretty rambunctious for little tikes but older kids will enjoy that he loves to play ball! Damion will need plenty of exercise in order to be a good boy. He is up to date on vaccinations, neutered and microchipped. His adoption fee is $250.00

She would love for her owners to be home more often than not. She would also do best in a home with a yard and a family that understands the grooming requirements of her breed. 

Adoption fee is $350 which includes her spay, microchip, vaccines current, deworming, flea treatment, grooming and dental. Apply at www.lovebugsrescue.org

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.

Hi everyone! My name is Ollie, aka Happy Puppy.

I was dropped at a shelter right before Christmas, it was going to be the worst Christmas ever. The people that left me at the shelter had never even given me a name, I was just the dog in the backyard. But they were all I knew and they were my family.

Turns out this was the best Christmas ever! A lovely lady from Animal Allies of Texas picked me up and I got to spend Christmas inside. The lights were beautiful, and there was wrapping paper to play in, and kids and people that gave me pets and smiled at me. I was in Heaven.

I was given a name, Ollie. My very own name. But sometimes my foster mom calls me Happy Puppy, and I've heard her call me a velcro dog. I'm not sure what that is, but I love her so much and am so thankful that she saved me that I stick by her side all the time. She says I'm a good boy. I follow her around and couldn't be happier. I watch her cook, I sit with her when she's working, I play in the backyard with her.

I am very protective of her. I'm learning that other people are nice too and I don't have to protect my foster mom from everyone. I bond very strongly with one person and need to be introduced slowly to others. I need to be in a home with someone that will continue to socialize me.

I also don't like it when mom leaves, was I abandoned again? I get anxious when I can't see mom but I am getting better as I get more confident.

There are kids in my foster home. They are fun too, but my foster mom is best.

There are also two cats in the house, I'd never met a cat before. They are cute and fuzzy, but no one told me that had daggers on their paws. I really want to be friends with them and don't understand why they don't always like to play with me. I get a little upset at this and I tell them so, I'm learning to give the cats their space.

I've also made friends with my foster dog sister. She's a lot bigger than me but we play in the backyard and go on walks. Walks are the best. I'm learning what a leash is and still have to work on my leash manners. I say hi to all the dogs in the neighborhood, a little too loudly according to mom. But I want to please my foster mom so much that I listen well and do what I'm told when corrected. I love chews so much, who knew that the world contained so many tasty treats. I will sit by mom while she's working on her computer all day, chewing on a chew and napping. I'm still in the puppy stage and don't always know what I can and can't chew on. But I promise I'll do my best.

I was born with a twisted pelvis. It doesn't cause me pain or stop me from doing anything, I can run and jump with the best of them. But you will see me hold my back right leg off the ground sometimes.

I have a little bit of growing to do, but I'm going to be on the small side. Small enough to be picked up and carried around, which is also the best. I fall asleep in my foster mom's arms. I honestly don't know how I got this lucky.

The only thing I need to complete my perfect life is a forever home. I need to be with someone that will continue to work on my training and socialization. I want to be the best dog for you. If you would like to meet me please contact AAT. I'd sure love to meet you!

And if you would like to volunteer to save more lives and foster cats or dogs, please go the Animal Allies of Texas website and inquire. If it wasn't for the kind lady who sprung me from the shelter, I might not be here to tell my story. Animal Allies of Texas (AAT) will educate you on what it takes to be a Foster Parent.
animal.name: Ollie

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.COMING SOON!

Bean is currently in training and will be available starting February 23, 2021.

Mom says that I have the prettiest brindle coat that she has ever seen! It is true, my pictures do not do me justice. I am a very smart and energetic pup, and I am learning some basic manners. My people are teaching me to walk on a leash and I love to sit for tiny dog biscuits. I am crate trained and happily go into my crate with a treat when my fosters parents are running people errands. I have NOT had one accident in the house, and I know what to do when we go outside. I like to bark when anyone new enters the house or whenever the garage door opens!

Since I am young and still learning to respect boundaries my forever home needs to have an experienced pet owner in it. My foster mom says that I would be a great running partner because of how well I am doing on a leash and I have such fun running off my energy (I like to sleep soundly through the night). I have not been introduced to these things called "cats" and I have no idea how I will respond to them. Since I am a large puppy, bigger kids would be great to play with. I would probably knock over a little human. If I had the opportunity to play with a dog my size, I think it would be a lot of fun!

I am looking forward to finding my forever home, because I really like attention and being petted and loved on. If you would like to meet me, please contact AAT. I would sure love to meet you!

And if you would like to volunteer to save more lives and foster cats or dogs, please go the Animal Allies of Texas website and inquire. If it wasn't for the kind lady who sprung me from the shelter, I would not be here to tell my story. Animal Allies of Texas (AAT) will educate you on what it takes to be a Foster Parent.

animal.description:
Blu has just arrived into Rescue. This dashingly handsome  German Shepherd is 4 years of age, born in July of 2016.  And yes, he is named for his Blue hue. He is a Blue German Shepherd color wise, which you don’t see very often.

Blu arrived into our care after his owner passed away suddenly and the surviving owner wasn’t well enough to care for Blu. Fortunately, he reached out to us for help. 


Blu seems to really enjoys having other dogs to play with. He loves to be near his people as well. When he naps near you he will make sure to be touching you in some way with his nose, foot or head. He gets anxious when he knows his human is leaving the house but once left alone in the house he will snooze on the couch and await your return. 

Blu seems to  prefers positive praise over treats as he isn’t very food motivated; which is good because this handsome fluff ball needs to lose a few pounds. Haha! He is at 115 lbs and our Vet would like to see him around 95-100 lbs.

His energy level is perfect for any adventure: jog at the park, afternoon on the couch, swim session at the dog park- He  just wants to do what you want to do.  This boy sure loves to visit Starbucks and get a puppuccino and pets. His favorite activity is visiting his dog friends for play time.  Blu is super social and has done well meeting dogs of all genders and sizes. He is potty trained. His recall is good and will only get better with practice. Blu is currently working on his leash manners. At bed time he likes to sleep next to his human. Though, as the night goes on, he gets hot and finds a cool spot on the floor nearby.

If you would like to adopt this handsome boy , please visit our website and apply today!

https://www.washingtongsd.org/adopt

Please note that we require a secure fenced yard.

Our hours are by appointment only. IF WE FIND YOU TO BE A GOOD MATCH YOU WILL BE CONTACTED typically within 72 hours. YOU WILL HEAR FROM US ONLY IF WE FIND YOU TO BE A GOOD MATCH FOR ONE OF OUR RESCUE ANIMALS AND OUR ADOPTION GUIDELINES/PROGRAM. WE MUST REVIEW A COMPLETED APPLICATION BEFORE A POSSIBLE APPOINTMENT IS ARRANGED. NO EXCEPTIONS. All visits with the puppies/dogs are by approved applications and appointments only.

* We reserve the right to refuse any adoption without justification and not all applications or inquiries may receive a response. *

Thank you for your interest in our rescue dogs.

animal.description:
Male, 9 years, pit bull X, 76 lbs

Jack Spade will make a wonderful family dog. Although he does have a few small behavioral issues (details below) that I believe would improve with a more experienced handler, Jack's overall demeanor is very calm and loving. Jack still has lots of pep in his step, and is rather active for a senior dog. He loves his walks, and seeing other people. His favorite place to be is cuddled on the couch surrounded by family. Jack does not jump, bark (even at the doorbell), and is 100% house trained. He is very well mannered overall, although we think perhaps sometimes has hearing issues, so can sometimes "ignore" commands. He likes the car, and has already learned to sit calmly on car rides. Jack also likes his crate and is happy to chill in there with the door open or closed on a regular basis. He is great with kids, very loving, but likely would do better with older children to start, who can read his signs around comfortability. 

One issue we have seen is that Jack can show aggression in heightened situations. Whether he becomes too excited through play with kids or other dogs, or overstimulated when he sees other dogs, he seems to have no awareness of his size, and can either scare, or injure (unintentionally through his body weight, never biting) those he is playing with. He has also shown aggression with other dogs in the home (never outside). We introduced him to an extended family pet and there were several acts of aggression (without injury). That being said the more comfortable Jack gets, the less this is an issue. 

Finally, Jack is extremely strong, and pulls on the leash during walks. An experienced handler could likely curb this behavior quickly with focused training. There appears to be evidence of prior leash training, which may just need to be refreshed. 

Jack would make an incredible companion for someone looking to minimize the work involved in training a new dog. He is very loving and relaxed overall and would easily slip into routine.

Our rescue is called BARCS. We are a registered Non Profit.
Our Website is www.barcsrescue.com. All our animals are posted on the website and updated often. If you would like to proceed we need an adoption application to be filled out. They can be found on our website. Once we receive your application, we will contact you to arrange a meeting with the pup you are interested in. 
We look forward to hearing from you

Name: Blue

Age: 1yr

Gender: Male

Breed: Weimaraner/Labrador Retriever mix

Weight: 47 lbs

Dog friendly: yes

Cat friendly: testing available upon request

Child friendly: y
es, older respectful children aged 5+ yrs

House trained: in progress

Crate trained: yes

Energy level: low-medium

Temperament: shy, scared easy going

Requirement: Not apartment appropriate

Adoption Fee: $400+tax

To adopt, go to:

www.mendingspirits.org/apply-to-adopt.html

From the Foster Family: Blue's former owners we not very nice. Blue came in with a form of non-contagious mange and the owner said he has had that since he was a pup but never treated it. He is coming along nicely and is doing very well. He has bonded with me right away and likes to be where I am at. He is in a decompression mode but has settled in very well for the first 24 hrs. he was in the recliner with me and fell asleep and laid in bed with me last night and is in the house with 5 other dogs where he is learning that everything is OK. He is very striking and handsome. He has such a wonderful Blue color and I am not sure what all he might be mixed with. This guy will need some extra loving to get him to feel safe but he's a gem.

About Me: My sister Lady Blue and I are so happy that our former not so nice owner brought us to a holding shelter in AL. Instantly, the holding shelter staff started to give me lotions and meds for my skin condition. I feel so much better. I wish I could tell everyone what breeds I am but I do like all the guessing. I have heard of Texas Blue Lacy dog, Char Pei, Lab, and Weimer. All are very good guesses. Once I get established and feel that I am loved, I am going to be the best dog you could ever hope for. I am looking for a family that will take some time with me to make sure I feel secure and loved and I am going to blossom. So, if you are looking for a handsome, good looking, blue dog, please lets meet and see how we connect. Thanks, Blue

We require an approved application to meet any of our dogs. We do not have a shelter location and will not arrange a meeting without an approved application.

We strive to make sure the bios provided for our dogs are complete and accurate; we do understand that mistakes happen, however, so if you absolutely cannot find the answer to your question in the dog's bio, you can contact us for more information.

We require a home visit for each dog we adopt out, so we adopt within a 2 hour radius of Dayton, OH. If you are outside of this radius, we encourage you to contact your local rescue or shelter.

Meet Blondie!

Blondie was found as a stray in Cleveland. She had been staying in an abandoned house until she was caught. Blondie was very scared and shut down at the kennel. We pulled her and she went right into a foster home. At first she wouldn’t move much from her safe spot on the couch other than for potty breaks and to eat. It’s pretty clear Blondie was neglected for a long time and only used for breeding and then dumped when they had no more use for her. Slowly but surely she started coming out of her shell and wagging her tail. She really loves to cuddle. She is the perfect lazy couch potato dog. She is shy when meeting new people but will warm up. She is crate trained and potty trained. 

Blondie is about 3yrs old, spayed, current on vaccines and microchipped.

Adoption fee is $250.00. 
Adoption application & home visit required.  Blondie requires a fenced in yard. Adopters must live within 30 miles of Cleveland.

Sweet little Indy is a playful Pitbull/Heeler Mix. She is about 11 weeks old (born about November 01, 2020) She weighed 15 pounds on her 10 week checkup. We except her adult weight to be approximately 50 to 65 LBS.. She and loves to run, play, and wrestle with her foster siblings. She has a beautiful, soft coat with adorable freckles and spots. She has a very expressive face and a playful personality. She can be scared in new situations and needs to be reassured that everything is okay. She is playful and loving to adults and children (over 8) and kind to cats (but she does like to bark at them). Indy has a big voice and lots of opinions. She needs very ACTIVE humans who will take her on daily walks and outdoor adventures. She will make a great companion dog as she is loyal, loving and always making sure her humans are okay. She follows her foster parents everywhere and always wants to be part of the action. She is a SNUGGLE bug and expects to sleep in your bed.. She is working on being potty trained but still has accidents. She is a PUPPY. Please have time to properly potty train her. She will need a home with a submissive but active doggy sibling for her to play with. She doesn't like to be left alone. She needs lots of love and chew toys and needs to be an inside dog with outside privileges. She will benefit from consistent training and positive reinforcement. Due to breed / size restrictions in rental property, Home Owners Only Need Apply! A secure 6ft plus fenced yard required. Indy is spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations. Are you ready for some puppy love? She is waiting for her forever family. OFFICE (more pictures to follow)
If you are interested in this dog or would like more information Please scroll down to the “MORE ABOUT US” button Click that . Then click on the adoption link and fill out the application.

Looking for someone to be your one and only? A dog to teach tricks to, take walks on, travel with? Why not Gemma?! This girl deserves the best second chance and we are committed to giving that to her! 

She learned the tricks in her video within a week of the foster having her. She is around 30lbs, so maybe 40lbs at a perfect healthy weight.

Pretty little Abby is one sassy girl! She is an approximately 3 year old, 10.14 pound (needs to lose a pound or two) mostly white, Chihuahua mix. She has darling apricot tipped ears and a cute little tan spot on her rump! Abby is shy and will need patience to blossom in her new home. We pulled her from a city shelter because she was terrified in that environment and was recovering from hernia surgery. It took her a couple days to quit hiding from the staff but once she came around she became a staff favorite. Abby is everything that is wonderful about the Chihuahua breed, a real sweetheart just waiting for a loving person! Adorable Abby loves to give you kisses, if she thinks she is going to get a treat she stands up on her back legs waiting in anticipation for the treat. Can you give her the time she needs to be her best self? Abby loves to "sit pretty" for a treat or your attention. She would be fine as an only dog if you work from home or are home full time. Abby favorite place to be is in your lap receiving and giving cuddles. This beautiful girl does enjoy the company of another dog similar in size and respectful of her space as she can be a DIVA. She is working on house training and prefers for you to go outside with her to do her business. Here at the sanctuary we use the command "Go Potty" before we go outside. She will run outside WITH you. She may need leash training. Due to her small size, she is not safe left alone outside!! She is spayed, current on vaccinations has been micro-chipped. No apartments. animal.description:
Name: Pina

Age: baby

DOB: 6/6/20

Gender: Male

Breed: Collie/Labrador Retriever mix

Weight: 43lbs

Dog friendly: yes

Cat friendly: testing available upon request

Child friendly:
Yes, older respectful children aged 5+ yrs, please

House trained: in progress, puppy

Crate trained: Testing available upon request

Energy level: Mellow likes to lay around

Temperament: easy-going loves petting mellow

Requirement: Not apartment appropriate

Adoption Fee: $500+tax

To adopt, go to:

www.mendingspirits.org/apply-to-adopt.html

From the Foster Family: Pina might be one of the most easy-going, mellow 7-month-old dogs I have ever fostered. He came from a bad situation where he and a momma dog with 5 puppies were outside all the time. The momma and 3 of her puppies and Pina were caught and brought to rescue. There are still 2 more puppies to be gotten. Pina is a very laid back, easy-going, good size dog. You go up to him and he just lays on his back for you to pet him. He slept in bed with me last night and was in the recliner yesterday just sleeping away. He has had a little bit of non-contagious mange by his eyes and nose that is healing up wonderfully. If you are looking for an easy-going dog that loves attention, Pina should be on your list to meet.

About Me: What a difference a month makes!!!! Just a month ago I was outside all the time and with a momma dog and her 5 pups. Mary came and got almost all of us. She was not able to catch 2 of the pups but said she will be going back to get them. We went to a rescue where there were all kinds of dogs and then loaded on a van and now I am here in MN. I am in a house with just 5 other dogs. I like that better. I can lay on the couch or a recliner or on the bed. These soft places are so much better than the ground all the time. I am only 7 months old but am an OLD soul and love to lay around and get petted and give out love. I had some sores around my eyes and nose but they are feeling so much better. Are you looking for a good, medium-sized, easy-going dog? I would love to meet you to see if we could be a match. Have a great day and I hope to meet you soon. Pina

Choose Copper, and you'll go far together! Meet Copper, a 3.5 year old, 75 pound Black and Tan Bloodhound. If you know and love the Bloodhound breed, you will adore Copper! He is a well rounded and happy boy who is ready to be part of a family. Copper is seeking a home with similar size and energy level dog friends, a securely fenced yard and supervised outside time with leashed runs, walks and hikes. While he is quiet most of the time, when he finds his voice it is impressive, and you can't miss it. Copper loves to play with other dogs and he runs with his ears flying in the wind. When he's tired he likes to snooze on a soft dog bed. Copper already knows Sit and is working on some other basic commands. He is housetrained and rides well in the car. If you are looking for a happy and loving hound to join your pack, Copper is ready to follow his nose right home!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.

animal.description:
THE FIRST STEP IN THE PROCESS IS SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION. WE CANNOT ANSWER EMAILS ASKING ABOUT A DOG'S AVAILABILITY. IF IT IS LISTED WITHOUT THE WORD "PENDING" IT MEANS IT IS AVAILABLE.

PLEASE COPY AND PASTE THIS LINK TO OUR APPLICATION:
https://tlps.wufoo.com/forms/the-little-pink-shelter-adoption-application/

Mary-Kate and Ashley. Kylie and Kendall. Venus and Serena. Add “Penny and Precious” to the mix and you get the All-Time Top Sister Pairs!!! Penny and Precious were dumped together way out in the country in very rural Arkansas, 2 sweet sisters whose dire situation was lost on them. Thankfully a kind woman took them in and cared for them for a bit, thinking maybe someone would come looking for them. But of course, no one did. So we got them into our program at the shelter we like to call "The Group Home" and they have been amazing us ever since.

We really want to keep these two beautiful sisters together simply because they are truly joined at the hip. They're the kind who "finish each other's sentences", take every step together without even thinking about it, seem to have inside jokes together and even seem to read each other's minds! Because of their bond, we're not sure whose hearts would break more if they were separated: theirs or ours. We're looking for a person or a family whose hearts can open wider than they ever thought possible to let these two sweet girls stay together for life. We know whoever does, will understand immediately just how special and beautiful their bond is.

Penny and Precious are super social with everyone -- they just love people, love to be petted and, if you think you're sitting in that chair alone think again because before you know it, "someone's" little paws will be in your lap nudging you to let her climb up, while "someone else's" little nose might be nudging you for another belly rub!  They're still puppies, still have their moments of puppy zoomies, and that means double trouble (in the cutest way).  But they're never underfoot and know how to give you space when you need it.   And of course they'll always be able to amuse themselves if you're too busy.   

Penny is the tri-colored girl and she’s a bit more the “brains of the operation”. Precious is mostly golden-and-white and is very much the little sister: she’s physically smaller, she’s a bit more the instigator at playtime, and she is very comfortable taking Penny’s lead. We guess they're about 10 - 12 months old and they’re very healthy girls. Penny weighs about 45 pounds and Precious weighs about 35 pounds. We have no way of knowing if they're actual littermates, half-sisters (female dogs can have multiple mates) or just sisters-from-another-mother, but we do know they're soul sisters who deserve to stay together. If your heart and home - - and pockets - - are big enough for 2 beautiful, loving sweethearts, please visit www.pinkshelter.org for more information about the adoption process. Full vetting AND spay included in their adoption fee. Transport fee is additional $140 each. IF YOU HAVE AOL or YAHOO PLEASE CHECK YOUR SPAM FILE FOR OUR RESPONSE

animal.description:
Request an application at homelesstoforever@gmail.com or apply via our website at www.homelesstoforever.com

Poor Olive. She's had a rough time. Olive was bought by her previous owner from a street vender selling her in a tiny cage. She was then passed on to a different home and eventually to a foster family with our rescue working on getting her a Forever Home. Little Olive ad bladder stone that was the size of her bladder and she had surgery to remove the stone.  Surgery was successful and she eats prescription food in order to not have further stones. However, Olive has issues with urination. The vet states she is unable to control her urination to a certain degree. She is able to wear diapers, but there is always work with her to try and train to use the potty pad. Olive is an intelligent, sweet little girl with a lot of personality. She does well with people of all ages. We are looking for a specific Forever Home and Family for Olive. We hope she can be either an only pet or that an other dog would be similar in size and not an alpha dog. We are searching for an adopter who either has experience with dogs who have had bladder stones and incontinence issues or who has the time and energy to learn.  We are looking for a Forever Family and Home where Olive will be happy and settled and enjoy a long life ahead of her. If you feel you are that special someone or family to offer Olive a Forever Home where she will have the time and resources spent on her and where she can enjoy life, feel free to apply to adopt her. Adoption donation: $300

No out of state applications and applications required prior to meet and greets.

All of our animals are fixed, chipped, and up to date on vaccinations. 

 LIKE our Facebook page for news, events, and new animals. www.homelesstoforever.com and www.Facebook.com/HomelessToForeverFoundation

animal.description:
Poodle was found as a stray. She was recently groomed so I assume dumped. She was pulled from the shelter August 28, 2020 after not being claimed. While you can tell she's been spoiled she wasn't taken care of medically. She is 10 lbs and ~8 years old.  Poodle needed a much needed dental. The dental xray showed she needed six teeth removed. She had mammary tumors in every mammary when we got her. She's had half removed. The report came back not cancerous. She is scheduled to have the rest removed on January 29th. The estimate is $800. She had giardia which is an intestinal parasite. She does randomly show back pain. Nothing showed up on her xray but her muscles are tense sometimes per the vet. We give her gabapentin when needed. The pill must be crushed or she will not eat it. She currently takes dasuquin ground up. She refuses a chew. She also takes Welactin fish oil. She would benefit with Adequan injections. She possibly may need back surgery in the future. The adopter should be prepared for the expense. She will need to be kept very slim to not add extra stress on her back. She does have one luxating patella but it does not cause any issues. She is heartworm negative, spayed, and microchipped. She's had numerous exams. She's up to date on vaccinations, flea prevention, and heartworm prevention. She needs regular grooming. She saw the ophthalmologist vet. He diagnosed her with keratitis. This is scarring of her eyes from allergies. She will be on Keterolac eye drops twice a day for the rest of her life. She doesn't care for the drops but allows you to do them. She possibly might need some lashes removed but the vet thought the drops would be enough. We will check in a few weeks. 
She will only eat can food. We tried several dry and she'd rather starve. She seems like a little diva. She hates dogs over 20 lbs with a passion. I don't see this changing since she's been around nice ones since August. She acts like everyone is beneath her. She does not like any chews. She will eat treats though. All pills must be crushed or she will refuse the food. She uses a potty pad when needed. She does love the baby pools and mud. In the beginning she was extremely nervous in the car. I assume after being dumped. She's much better now and even wants to stick her head out the window for air. She's good at the vet. She walks good on the leash and loves walks. I see her on a dog bed glaring at her servants. A few times if we reached for her she's been nippy. I assume she's painful. I would instead get her on a leash and then I have no issues. This rarely happens. Due to this I'd recommend no children. She comes to me to be picked up when coming back inside without issues. The issues usually are getting out the car or a crate. She is located in New Orleans, LA but we adopt out of state.

Need a lovely girl to make your family complete? Meet our sweet and Beautiful Hazel. She is a 7-8 month old, Red hound/ Beagle mix. Hazel family was told she was a Dachshund/ Min Pin mix and they expected her to be about 16 pounds. At 7 months she is already 28 pounds! Due to Covid, Hazel has not been socialized outside the home. She is wary of strangers but should blossom in a home with a family to give her attention. Hazel LOVES to PLAY. She loves to play fetch with tennis balls and wooden sticks. At night, Hazel loves her belly rubbed at night time and she’s also a big cuddle bug. She can easily switch from being an active dog to a lapdog. Hazel knows a few tricks- she knows how to sit, stay, lay down, and shake. She also knows how to use the doggy door and is potty trained. Since Hazel is considered a “quarantine” dog, it takes her time to warm up to strangers. When she is unfamiliar with strangers and noises, she’ll bark at first. She’s an ACTIVE dog so she likes DAILY exercise. When she’s indoors, she loves to play with stuffed toys and chew on ropes. She can easily switch from being an active dog to a lapdog. She also knows how to use the doggy door and is potty trained. When she is unfamiliar with strangers and noises, she’ll bark at first. She needs a good amount of attention but once she is comfortable and feels safe, she is a great companion for someone who wants a constant companion a family situation is best suited for her. She will need a home that include another playful dog and is used to playing with a multi-poo. A person at home with her most of the time is a must. She is a great companion for someone who has the time and attention to give her. She is spayed, microchipped and up to date on vaccinations. Do you have room in your heart and home for Hazel? animal.description:
Meet Creed

Creed is a 4 year old bull dog mix with a very friendly personality. He likes everyone he meets and is very good with dogs and cats however does become possessive of objects when comfortable in a home. So he might be better as an only dog. He is house trained. Creed also loves to play with his toys. He is medium energy and loves playing, hugging, and going for walk and greets everyone along the way. He does all this without being a particularly needy guy. Creed does prefer living with a man and we hope to find him that perfect home. We have placed Creed in a home with a women and man and he gravitates toward the man and becomes possesive. For this reason we are going to require him going to a home with a single man preferable a little active. Sometime in the past he was injured and it was not treated so his one rear leg does not have full use and never will. This does not stop him from going on walks. We put a doggy boot on that foot during the day if he is going to be out and about so that he does not rub the toes on that foot raw. It is easy to put the boot on and he will leave it on without any problems. He seems to realize it keeps the foot from being rubbed and makes it easier to walk and play. He is an all around fabulous guy who needs a buddy to hang with. To see how well he uses his leg you can watch the short video.

For more info call Pet Adoption League.208-366-1359

animal.description:
Age: 10 months (as of 1/14/21)
Weight: 49.6 lbs (as of 1/14/21)

Location: RI

This dog has been spayed/neutered, is up to date on shots, on heartworm preventative and is microchipped.

Meet Chance! He looks to be about 10 months old and likely a German Shepherd mix. Chance and his brother, Trey, were found as strays and have been living in the pound for the last two months. While we don't know much about Chance, he seems to have the potential to be a model canine citizen. He's affectionate, outgoing, even-tempered and like most puppies, can be hyper at times but settles quickly. He does well in outdoor playgroup with his brother and other pups. Beyond playtime with other dog friends, Chance loves to go for walks and runs and play fetch. He has had some exposure to visiting children and gets very excited to see them, but we can't be sure how he would do living with kids full-time since he hasn't been with them much. Chance can be a little vocal and sometimes demand barks.

As with all of our rescue pups, we would recommend that Chance and his new human(s) attend some dogs training classes together. They are a great way to help teach him essential commands, reinforce these skills, and get some socialization time with other dogs -- all while continuing to enhance the bond between pet and parent. He's still just a puppy, so he will need some practice with house-, crate-, and leash training. Chance appears to be an intelligent dog, so he seems like he would respond well to training.

Ready to take a "Chance" on this sweet pup? Fill out an application today!

Medical Note: This dog tested positive for exposure to ehrlichia while in SOS foster care. This does not mean that this dog had ehrlichia. This dog is/has been asymptomatic while in SOS care and was preventatively treated with a 28-day course of doxycycline. Please see here for more information on ehrlichia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ehrlichiosis_(canine). Please check with your vet if you should have any questions or concerns about this condition, and discuss any concerns you may have with your SOS Adoption Counselor.

Adoption Fee: $585

To apply for this dog, fill out an adoption application on our website: www.sosarl.org/aa/

**Additional info you should know - For most of our dogs, we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each of our dogs as an individual and do our best to describe and place them based on personality not breed label. Some dogs may not yet be in New England, nor ready for immediate adoption. There may be additional vetting, quarantine, waiting periods and/or fees depending upon your state of residence. If you have questions or concerns on any of this, you can discuss this with your Adoption Counselor.

*PLEASE NOTE DOROTHY NEEDS AN ADULT ONLY HOME NO CHILDREN, AND SHE NEEDS TO BE THE ONLY PET/DOG AND SHE WILL DO BEST WITH SOMEONE WHO WORKS FROM OR IS RETIRED *

Dorothy is an affectionate, playful, happy girl. She loves to watch musicals and was named after Dorothy in Wizard of Oz. She loves to snuggle with blankets and enjoys bully sticks and bones.

She is a seven-year-old dachshund and pug mix, Dorothy is a pugshund! She loves being with "her" people; she will be a bit shy at first, but once she learns she can trust you, she will open up, and be a love bug! Her favorite things are snuggling, going on walks, kisses on her cheeks, and getting all the attention and love she deserves; Dorothy is a little princess.

At home, she spends a good time of her day snoozing next to her foster dad in the home office; he says she is a great co-worker!

Dorothy is house trained (knows to use pee pads if needed) she doesn't chew on things and is good roaming free if left alone; she doesn't love her crate, but she uses it sometimes.

She likes people in general, but a family of adults only would be best since she has some sensitive areas she can get snappy. Dorothy has some sensitive areas where you need to approach softly, like her ears.

Dorothy loves car rides, walks nicely on a leash, and she will chase a squirrel if she sees one!

She would do best in a home where she is the only pet in the house since she doesn't like other pets much.

If you want to learn more about Dorothy, you can contact her foster mom at denisev4@icloud.com

Could you be Dorothy's new person? The Adoption Fee for Dorothy is: $275.00 + $45.00 for a health certificate if going over state lines (required by law). TRANSPORTATION HELP! If you see a furbaby that would be a match for your family, please don't let distance stand in the way of your adoption. LPDR can work with you to have a volunteer transport to assist with transportation or refer you to a paid transport.

animal.description:
ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/10352

Hi! My name is Spudd! Spudd is a handsome, tall, gentle and quite spoken gentleman. He's guessed to be a 2 year old hound mix. Spudd says I am a sweet boy and I currently weigh about 66 lbs. 

Spudd would be a perfect running or biking partner, he loves the outdoors and has a beautiful stride. Click here to see him in action! 

I was found on the side of the road by a good Samaritan who saw my need to go to the vet asap. She noticed I had a GPS and personal collar on. She went home to gather some towels and when she returned I was waiting for her but missing my GPS and personal collar. The Good Samaritan could not imagine what I thought when the owner arrived but then turned around and left me on the side of the road. Animal Control was called and took me to the vet where I was checked out with only a case of road rash on the left side of my body. So, this is the beginning of my journey with OPH. 

Spudd does very well on a leash and LOVES to sniff everything when going on walks. Spudd has not had any accidents nor marked in the house and will go to the door when he wants to go out. He has been introduced to the Foster's 3 personal dogs and 1 cat with no reaction. He does not seem to recognize commands like Sit yet but learning Outside and Potty easily and now working on Come. 

Because of his height, he is the perfect candidate to be a counter surfer! Spudd accepts the crate with little protest (whines) but will settle within minutes. He does not jump on people and loves to be around people. He has not been introduced to small children.

 His loves to go on walks and the only reaction on walks was the sound of a diesel truck. He has yet to interact play with the Fosters personal dogs or with toys. Spudd is a gentle soul who loves to be scratched. Spudd is waiting for an adopter who will give him a loving home forever now matter what... Is that special someone you?
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description:
Urgent will be going to shelter February 1rst. It is an urgent call. Never been around children or cats. From the lady who adopted him 2 years ago:

"Sam is a 4-year-old Great Dane/Greyhound mix. He is black, with white sprinkles, and weighs in at about 75 pounds. He loves to run, walk, and play with his toys and bones, and other dogs. As a puppy, Sammy was attacked by some older dogs, leaving him with some subtle scars you may notice on his neck. When I first got him, he was skittish, and not at all trusting. But, with time and patience, he has come into his own, developed an amusing personality, learned to trust me, and considers himself my protector. Sam is smart, stubborn, funny, athletic and enjoys conversation. By conversation, I mean he likes to talk. He talks when he’s hungry, when he wants to go out, or when he just wants some attention. (I have never had a dog do this before.) He has a loud and deep bark that would scare away any intruder. Sam has a sensitive stomach and is allergic to chicken. I give feed him about 6 cups a day of “sensitive stomach” dry food, along with 6 or seven hard-boiled eggs, throughout the day. Sam has his boundaries. For example, he prefers not to be bothered when he’s trying to sleep. It makes him grumpy and grumbly. Oh, and he has an underbite that can make for some messy eating. But he does clean up after himself. Pet his face, rub his ears and muzzle and he’ll be yours forever. He is up to date with his vaccines. "

animal.description:
"Everyone needs a heart full of love and a life full of kisses..." Wait, that's me! My name is Kisses and I am a 3 month old, 15 pound Shepherd mix girl looking for the perfect family to call my own. I am a typical playful puppy with lots of energy, so I am looking for a family who is active, ready to play, and has plenty of toys to keep me entertained. I am working hard on potty training and kennel training, so I need someone who can provide me with the structure and training necessary to help me grow into the best pup I can be! I am great with other dogs and humans of all ages. In fact, I would prefer a home with some playful dog or human siblings, as well as a fenced-in yard in which we can play together (no apartments for me please). If you have been looking for a new love of your life, then why not apply for me, Kisses?

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Lincoln (TX) is a male Chihuahua mix rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Lincoln is 2 years old at the time of intake in January 2021. Lincoln is good with people and other dogs. Lincoln was cruelly abandoned in a backyard when his owners moved away. He was locked in a crate with no chance at all of survival without food, water or shelter. Fortunately, neighbors heard Lincoln and tried to get the authorities to step in and help him. When no one came after one day, two days, three days, our volunteer removed Lincoln and brought him to safety. We can't change the horror of Lincoln's past, but we can definitely change his future. If you can open your heart, home and life to Lincoln and give him the fantastic future we promised him, please apply online to adopt Lincoln (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

animal.description:
***If you are interested in adoption please go to our website at www.emmetcountyanimalshelter.org to complete the dog adoption application.***

Ahhhh those eyes! Those crystal blue beautiful eyes! Meet Jakob Black or JB as we call him. Appropriately named after a movie character who is equally as handsome as this gorgeous guy! Not to mention they both have the same howl! Jakob was found at large by 3 different community member successfully escaping from each of them to continue his jaunt across the county. Most likely looking for love since we are sure he knows he is handsome and the fact that he was an intact male! When he was picked up and put in to impound not only did that stop his escaping and running around looking for hot chicks it also took care of the intact male part! In the same instance he is now becoming a well mannered young man that is eager for some attention and affection. Jakob likely hasn't received a whole lot of training in his young life however he is an eager learner and is picking up on commands nicely while he stays here with us. He is a very big boy so a family with small children isn't a good mix as JB is still learning how to control his enthusiasm! Jakob does listen however he would benefit from a confident and experienced dog owner that knows how to communicate with an over zealous dog. Jakob keeps a clean kennel and hasn't shown any issue with the dogs coming and going around him. We have not cat tested him yet so we are not sure about the feelings he has towards felines. Jakob has been neutered, vaccinated, micro-chipped and wormed. His adoption fee is $275.00
animal.name: JB (Jakob Black)

animal.description:
Merlin is officially available for adoption now.    More than a pretty face, we will only consider a family that has the energy and time for a young high energy puppy.  Merlin is maybe 10 months old and ALL pup and totally deaf collie mix.   He is super High energy but not neurotic.   He now has basic commands using hand signals and crates beautifully.   He no longer attempts to herd the kids but it would be best he either has older mindful kids, or a family with a solid history of working with herding dogs, and fully accepting he may make mistakes and grab pants.  He MUST be formally enrolled in positive trianing classes and He will NEED another young high energy dog to play with him.  This is not negotiable.  He takes dog correction very well, and has been fine with the cats and chickens here at GDU.   He is a special boy that has captured our directors heart and We owe it to him to be picky in his placement.   A physically fenced yard is a MUST.  Underground fencing is not an option.   Please do not email asking for an exception to this.  I assume someone saw him as a gorgeous puppy, did nothing with him, and gave him up when he started herding children out of boredom.  As long as he gets an appropriate amount of exercise, this is not an issue.   He is being fostered at GDU HQ by our Animal Behavior Specialist who absolutely adores him.   If you are interested and meet these qualifications set forth, please fill out an app.  We will not respond to applications which do not meet the stated needs.
At the time you are seeing this post, Merlin is still available for adoption. But please know that we may be working on multiple applications already, and any one of them could be approved at any time. Please READ THIS ENTIRE DESCRIPTION and complete an adoption application, if you are interested in any of our animals. Application at www.greendogsunleashed.org   If you send an inquiry to ask if the dog is still available, or just tell us you are interested, your inquiry will not be answered. FILL OUT AN APPLICATION. We can do NOTHING without that. No, we cannot tell you if he would be a match for your family without seeing an application.  PLEASE KEEP READING for info.

*/*/* PLEASE NOTE:  The first communication you will receive after completing an application will be an email response, which will have instructions on how to proceed. Please check your inbox AND spam folders for the next 48 hours, for this email. We will not begin processing an application without the information requested in that email. */*/*

We are happy to consider applicants from out of state on most dogs. Please read the description to see if this dog is an exception.  If the applicant is approved to adopt, they MUST be willing to come to our location in Troy, VA, for a meet and greet. If all parties agree that the pup and family are a good fit,  they would take the pup home at that time.

For more information about our mission and for an APPLICATION for adoption, please go to www.greendogsunleashed.com.

GDU does ask a minimum adoption fee of $300.00. This does not even come close to covering all expenses created by animals while in rescue. We are funded solely by the angels and volunteers willing to donate time and finances. This minimum fee includes DAPP, rabies if age appropriate,, heartworm test and preventative, if age appropriate, and flea and tick treatment, as well as neutering or spaying, if the animal is medically sound to undergo surgery.  In an attempt to avoid tummy upset from a sudden change of food, the foster family may include a small, transitional bag of the food the dog/puppy has been eating. And if the dog/puppy has grown attached to a special item (like a toy or blanket), they may send that along, as well.

*/*/*  Young puppies will receive age-appropriate vaccines, and will be spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Adopters may be required to provide additional puppy boosters and at 16 weeks of age, a rabies vaccine. Future annual vaccines, testing and monthly heartworm preventative are REQUIRED, and will be the financial responsibility of the adopter.

animal.description:
Breed: Beagle X
DOB: 8/2006
Gender: female
Altered: yes
Coat: medium
Size: medium
Color(s): white/brown/black
Description:
Hi, I'm Trixie a Beagle X in need of a new home with my 'brother' Polo. We're a bonded pair and need to be adopted together. We're currently in a great foster home together, but what we really want is a forever home being showered with love and cherished as members of the family.

We ride great in the car and get to go on errands with our foster mom. I have a fancy 'ride', I think they called it a stroller, when we go on faster walks with our foster mom's dog.

Our foster mom provided some of our traits that she has observed since fostering us. I need a home with no children. I'm fecal incontinent but I will let you know when I have to outside to urinate. My feces is firm so my foster mom just picks it up. My back right leg is a bit wobbly and weaker than the left so i fall over at times. My front is very stiff from bearing so much of my weight my foster mom massages me daily to try and loosen it up. I don't hear much and I don't have good sight either, but I don't bump into things as I'm able to rely on my nose to guide me. Although I have a good appetite, I'm picky with my treats. I'm also demanding when my meals are being prepared and I bark non-stop. I want to be in the kitchen and can get underfoot which isn't good as I can't see and could get stepped on. I go on daily walks a 1/4 to 1/2 a mile slowly to keep my legs in shape. After that I love riding in the dog stroller for rest of the walk. I do not care to be crated.

If you're looking for two great dogs, please fill out an online application to meet us.

Additional information: *Needs Adult Only Home *Special Needs

Volunteers report that she walks well on leash and is probably house-trained. Lyka will approach someone new, especially if they have treats in their hand! They also mention that she enjoys petting. German Shepherd Dogs are considered to be very intelligent and can make wonderful canine companions. Lyka, at a young five years of age, is still full of life even though she is considered to be a senior dog. As a senior dog, she qualifies for our Senior for Seniors Program in which if an adopter is sixty years old or more, then the adoption is totally free! As well, past and present military members can adopt for free. Lyka is a gorgeous looking dog who needs a new fur-ever home where she can feel loved and secure. Our veterinary partner estimates Legend to be 5-6 years old at the time of intake in January 2021. Legend is good with people and other dogs. Legend was found in a rural area of Texas literally starving to death. He was dazed and confused and was not going to survive on his own in the middle of nowhere. Rosie is a bit down since she learned she must diet to shed some extra pounds, but this sweet, quiet 8 year old will make a wonderful addition to a loving family. Rosie is very low key, enjoys her nap time and likes being outdoors exploring new surroundings.  She has no trouble getting around at all, and when she loses some weight she’ll be light on her feet!  She gets along with people and dogs but she’d really love some one-on-one encouragement along with a few walks to get into shape. Rosie is not a barker or howler. We suspect she has led a neglected life which shows by the condition of her skin.  She has either a flea allergy or a food allergy but we are treating whatever it is and she’s will most likely regrow the fur that’s missing on her lower back.  Rosie also has some hearing loss, but she can certainly hear the dinner bell!
We love our seniors. We hope you do too. Rosie just needs a little attention and love and she will thrive.  Could you be her hero?

Baloo is a handsome, happy Australian Shepherd who is ready for his forever home.  He is 1 year old, weighs 55 pounds, and he has a gorgeous red and white coat.  Baloo is housebroken, crate-trained and is learning his basic obedience commands.  He is a great passenger in the car but his leash walking skills need work!
Baloo loves people.  He is a high Velcro, high energy guy who loves attention and loves to play ball, play with his toys and run, run, run.  Baloo was recently introduced to agility and he loved it!  He still has a lot of puppy in him, and he will counter surf and jump up on people when he thinks he can get away with it!  Baloo also loves to play with other dogs, and romping and wrestling with other dogs are some of his favorite things to do. When he finally settles at the end of the day, this big goof naps with his pals, looks for someone to pet him, and just enjoys everyone’s company.  Baloo has not been exposed to cats.
The ideal home for Baloo is full of fun, fun and more fun.  A fenced yard and another energetic, playful dog are important, children should be over the age of 12, and his new family should be committed to a solid training regimen for him.  Baloo is a big goofy “puppy” who is ready for a great home with great pals and great training.  If your family would be a great match apply today!  Baloo is fostered in Frederick, MD.

animal.description:
Personality: Happy Gilmore is named for his super social and wiggly, excitable demeanor. He loves meeting new people but is still learning to not go overboard with his excitement (my human friend give me treats when I greet them like a gentleman and keep my paws on the floor). He is often so wiggly that he hurt his tail from wagging it too hard! Happy is looking for a family that is active and would love to take him on long walks and runs regularly. He would also benefit from a family that can guide him in his manners and learn to be calm. Happy is very food and tennis ball motivated so he aims to please! Happy loves to play fetch and it's a great way to tire him out. In his down time he LOVES to cuddle up with his friends. 

History: He came to us from the central valley. 

Dog/Cat Skills: Happy participates in playgroup daily. He often explores the yard and engages in chase play. He has shown a discomfort with more tense, forward behavior, especially from male dogs, and may correct or target them. He has shown to do best with relaxed, social females and does like to engage in some calm wrestle play. He can also become overly excited with vocal play. Happy is best with social, calm, tolerant dogs who can greet and play politely. Happy has shown hyper focus and willingness to chase cats. 

Leash Skills: Happy pulls while walking on a leash and would benefit from the use of a front clipping harness. He has shown some barrier and leash frustration with dogs displaying tense behavior, and does not always meet dogs comfortably on leash. We are working on this by redirecting him with treats or toys. 

Medical: Happy arrived at HSSV with trauma to the tip of his tail. Due to his habit of wagging his tail vigorously and hitting the walls with the tip of his tail, he repeatedly traumatized the tip of the tail until it became devitalized. He had also caused painful sores along the sides on the last 3rd of his tail from wagging it against walls. To treat his wounds and relieve his pain, it was necessary to amputate a portion of his tail. He is recovering and healing from the surgery very well. Happy is also healing from ear infections that are currently being treated. 

Ready to meet Happy Gilmore ? Fill out the form to request an appointment Primary Color: Brown Secondary Color: White Weight: 53lbs Age: 1yrs 6mths 4wks Animal has been Neutered

animal.description:
Snuggles is a sweet gal who found herself in a home with too many other pets. She and just one other were not getting along, so Snuggles found herself needing rescue. She is a great girl and very snuggly. She is unsure herself and her surroundings and will need an understanding home where she can adjust slowly and build her confidence to be the great, well adjusted girl we have seen glipses of! We were told she was chihauhau/poodle, but there might be some other DNA in there as well. We can't be certain of breeds! We are certain that she deserves a great home with a lap she can snooze on and a home she can blossom in! Because we are foster based, we require an approved application before a meet and greet can be scheduled. We think that is fair to our fosters so every meet and greet has the potential to result in an immediate adoption. The application is available on the rescue website and can be completed online. We work with many rescues and strive to find every rescued dog in our care a great home. Sometimes that means transferring that pet to another location where adoption may be more likely. We currently have partners in New York, Pennsylvania, and Vermont.

If you are interesting in meeting any of our pets, the process is to complete an application. It can be downloaded as a pdf document from our website and submitted by email to WindyRidgeRescue@gmail.com as a scanned document or as photos OR can be completed entirely online. Both links are in the header of our website.

Because we are foster based, we require an approved application to schedule a meet and greet. We feel that is fair to our fosters and rescues so every meet and greet can result in an adoption.

We do not have set adoption fees for dogs, but hope adopters will donate generously so we can rescue more. The medical care for every dog can easily exceed the adoption donation. Average adoption fees for dogs in the area range from $175 up to $450.

We ask for a minimum adoption donation of $50 for cats regardless of age. Each cat is up to date on vaccinations, dewormer, and microchipped. Larger donations are always welcome so we can rescue more. Medical care for each cat easily exceeds the minimum donation.

As with every rescue, our resources are limited and the need for rescue help is unlimited. Your generosity helps us to rescue more.

Adopting or fostering for a rescue frees up a space where a new rescue can reside.

If you can't adopt or foster, than please consider donating.
